title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: vi's ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, milk and eggs.
Mix well. Add salt and pepper. Shape into loaf and place in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Lower heat if loaf becomes too brown.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Then chop along with the eggs.
Mix chicken, eggs, soup and broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in pan, then mix flour, milk and butter.
Pour on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: canned beets
directions: You can put onions if you like.

title: salsa
directions: Cook tomatoes and hot peppers down.
Add other ingredients and cook 5 minutes.

title: chicken breast in lemon sauce
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken and garlic in margarine 4 to 6 minutes, turning once, until chicken is brown.
Add apple juice and sprinkle with pepper.
Heat until hot.
Sprinkle with mushrooms.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar; set aside. Combine broccoli, raisins, pecans, cheese, and a small amount of purple onion; add mayo mixture and mix well. Serve and enjoy!

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: To measure flour, stir, then lightly spoon into cup.
Measure flour, sugar, salt and soda into large mixer bowl; stir to blend thoroughly.
Add butter, yogurt, eggs and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Beat at slow speed of mixer until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat at medium speed of mixer for 4 minutes, scraping down sides of bowl frequently.
Remove beaters and stir in lemon peel.
Turn into well-greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake in oven at 300° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter; blend well.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: courtney's favorite cooked apples
directions: Wash and peel apples; cut into bite size chunks.
Put water and apples in saucepan; cover and cook on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in cinnamon and sugar; cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: salad dressing biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Roll out; cut and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 500° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Remove loose papery outside skin from garlic head without separating the cloves.
Slice off the top 1/2-inch.
Wrap in small square of foil and roast 40 minutes until garlic is very soft.
Unwrap and cool slightly.
Separate cloves and peel.

title: august harvest casserole
directions: Steam veggies until tender.
In a greased casserole, layer rice and veggies.
Top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: chili and enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add other ingredients, except water and cheese to the meat.
Cook until thickened.
Dip tortillas in hot water.
Put spoonful of chili meat in tortilla and roll up.
Put in baking dish.
Put the balance of chili over tortillas.
Cover with grated cheese.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: avocado pie
directions: Blend all ingredients very thoroughly; use blender or the high speed of a Mixmaster.
Take the smooth, light mixture and scoop immediately into a preformed graham cracker crust (spread it out evenly with a spatula).
It sets up rapidly.
Make 2 pies at once and freeze one for later.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add peanuts.
Cook until mixture darkens.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, baking soda and vinegar.
Stir quickly and pour on buttered large cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: new mashed potatoes
directions: In bowl cook unpeeled potatoes, margarine and 2 tablespoons water, covered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes, until tender.
Stir twice during cooking.
With masher, mash lightly.
Stir in broccoli, pepper and salt.
Top with cheese.
Melt 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving about 185 calories, 8 g fat, 7 mg cholesterol and 270 mg sodium.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain and set aside.
Combine the next 8 ingredients.
Cover and cook sauce over low heat for 1 hour.
Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain; place on paper towels and squeeze until barely moist.
Combine spinach, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg.
Stuff manicotti shells with spinach mixture; arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Pour tomato sauce over manicotti.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: world's greatest sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, salt, oleo, oil and vanilla; add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Drop with teaspoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 330° for 15 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: i don't have time to cook
directions: Using microwave directions, make potatoes.
Heat up green beans in microwave 12 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Add butter and heat up. Put prefried pattie or two in microwave for 2 minutes (one minute on each side).

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend on high for 30 seconds. Scrape sides of blender, then blend for 30 seconds more until smooth.
Pour into a lightly greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: ham or chicken quiche
directions: Divide chicken or ham, green pepper, onion and cheese.
Place in pie shells.
Top each with 1 tablespoon flour and 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour half into each shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mrs. santa's raspberry salad
directions: In medium bowl, evenly sprinkle unflavored gelatin over 1/2 cup water; let stand 1 minute to soften gelatin slightly.
Stir in raspberry flavored gelatin and 2 cups boiling water, stirring until gelatin completely dissolves.
Add pineapple, pecans and frozen raspberries (with syrup), stirring and using spoon to break up fruit.
Refrigerate until gelatin mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon (gelatin may not need to be refrigerated if raspberries are frozen solid).
Spoon 1/2 of gelatin mixture into 8-cup mold.
Gently spread sour cream over gelatin 1/2-inch from side of mold.
Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream. Cover mold; refrigerate until set, at least 3 hours.
To serve, unmold gelatin onto chilled platter.
Garnish with holly leaves. Makes 12 servings.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine cream cheese and potatoes; mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange cool whip salad
directions: Mix
pineapple	and jello.
Add in cottage cheese.
Mix gently, then add oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place one piece of chicken, boned side up, between 2 layers of clear plastic wrap.
Working from the center to the edges, pound lightly with meat mallet to about 1/4-inch thick.
Repeat with rest of chicken.

title: polly's potato patties
directions: Mix together the potatoes and onion.
Form into flat patties. Lightly grease a nonstick skillet with the margarine.
Fry the patties on one side and then the other until browned.
Add a dash of salt and pepper to taste.

title: cold spiced fruit
directions: Cut orange slices in half; place in water and simmer until rind is tender.
Drain well.
Drain canned fruit; reserve all pineapple juice, half of apricot and peach juice.
Combine juices, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, cloves and jello.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over mixed fruit.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: lemon rice and peas
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add rice, cover and simmer until water is absorbed, 30 to 40 minutes.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add cumin and mustard seed and cook, stirring, until mustard seed begins to pop.
Add scallions and cook until softened, approximately 1 minute.
Add cooked rice, peas, cashews, soy sauce, turmeric and cayenne.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serve wrapped in tortillas.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill a few hours before serving.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on bed of lettuce leaves. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Pat firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a small or large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Spread sour cream on cheese cake.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Crush chips up with hands.
Layer as follows:
chips, meat, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, taco sauce and top with sour cream.
Serve in a flat bowl.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar and let set for 20 minutes.
Mix together with flour, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add this mixture to apples, then beat together by hand eggs, vanilla, oil and walnuts.
Add this mixture to apples and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Pour topping over cake as soon as it boils.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Soak chillies in cold water and remove seeds.
Grate cheese. In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place a layer of chillies across the bottom.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the chilli layer.
Beat eggs, flour, salt and milk; pour over cheese.
Layer the rest of the chillies over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and zigzag with tomato sauce over the top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg yolks.
Then add coconut extract, milk, almond, flour, coconut and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in medium saucepan until thick (like cooked cereal).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, then eggs. Beat thoroughly.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Knead well on lightly floured surface.
Place in bowl; cover and let rise. Punch down.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli until very tender.
Cool; pure in food processor.
Saut onion in butter along with flour, garlic, basil, salt and pepper until onion is transparent, but not browned.
Add broccoli, evaporated milk and milk.
Heat to boiling point.
Serve hot with French bread and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken delight
directions: Put broccoli on bottom, then chicken, potatoes, carrots, soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Bake at 370° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Whip 1 pint of whipping cream and fold in.
In a 9 x 13 dish, layer wafers and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mix over these.
Make another layer of bananas and wafers.
Pour rest of mix over them.
May top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Spread pecans on bottom of pie crust.
Pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until firm in center.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl or a plastic bag that seals tightly.
Allow chicken to remain in the dressing for 2 hours or overnight, refrigerated.
Discard dressing.
Grill 5 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: leslie's famous fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into a bowl, containing the remaining ingredients.
Stir until melted and shiny.
Pour into a 6 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool to room temperature and cut into squares before refrigerating.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter to a cream. Add egg yolks and beat well. Add milk, nutmeg, salt, baking powder, soda and flour. Add egg whites. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add diced apples.
Add eggs, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Bakes nicely in Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans (probably won't take 1 hour in two pans).
Drizzle confectioners sugar icing over warm cake (about 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons milk).

title: mexican taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Put half of crushed corn chips in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Add olives and other half of corn chips.

title: spinach dip and pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix soup mix, sour cream and thawed spinach together thoroughly.
Take pumpernickel bread and cut out center to make bread look like a large bowl.

title: danish fruit cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Test by toothpick. Use a Bundt pan.

title: self-saucing apple pudding
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg, oil and vanilla, blending only until smooth.
Layer an 8 1/2 x 12-inch baking pan with cut up apples.
Sprinkle a little sugar, flour and cinnamon over them.
Add the cake mixture.
Combine brown sugar and hot water, pour over butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix with a wooden spoon. Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs and oil and then add blueberries. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mint cookies
directions: Place dough around 1 or 2 wafers (mint wafers from Fannie May). Press pecan on top. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Cook all together.
Bring to boil and boil for 3-5 minutes (hard stage).
Place graham crackers in bottom of cookie sheet, single layer.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5-10 minutes until bubbly.
Break into pieces.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan, cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: macaroni shells with cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Heat milk and soup.
Cook in microwave until hot.
Drain macaroni and add to soup mixture and serve.

title: sweet sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, crumbs, salt or beef granules, pepper and eggs.
Add chopped onion and 1/2 of the tomato soup. Form into a loaf and pour topping over all.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat together pineapple, sugar and Jell-O.
Cool until thick. Fold in whipping cream, then bananas.
Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine
cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk and mix well. Pour small
amount
over
egg yolks; mix well and add to milk mixture. Cook
in
double boiler until thickened.
Add butter and
vanilla and
pour
in
pie shell.
Top with meringue and sprinkle meringue
with
the
of peanut butter and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lentils with spinach
directions: Trim spinach and wash well.
Tear leaves into bite-size pieces and set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine water, lentils (picked over and rinsed), carrot, 1/4 finely chopped onion, garlic cloves and bay leaf; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; partially cover and simmer until lentils are tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Drain and discard bay leaf.
Return lentils and vegetables to the saucepan.
Add the reserved spinach, olive oil, salt and pepper. Cook over medium-low heat until the spinach wilts and the lentils are heated through, about 2 minutes.

title: near-boomless baked beans
directions: Parboil beans in an 8-quart kettle with baking soda for 3 to 5 minutes, then rinse beans thoroughly.
Cover beans with fresh water and continue cooking for 30 minutes, or until skins split. Drain well and rinse with cold water.
Put beans back in 8-quart kettle and add salt, spices, bacon and chicken broth.
Simmer until beans are soft.
Add molasses, brown sugar and maple syrup. Remove from stove and place beans in a 3-quart greased baking dish or bean pot.
Cover and bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 to 2 hours until beans have a nice brown color.
Stir occasionally and add water or broth if needed, so beans don't dry out.
Makes 12 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake 25 minutes or until done in 350° oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large loaf pan in oven.
Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk; pour over melted butter.
Top with peaches.
Sprinkle peaches with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini skillet
directions: Stir and cook vegetables in margarine over high heat until tender, about 15 minutes. Top with cheese before serving.
Great cooked in skillet on top of stove, a time saver.
(I omit the cheese.)

title: rocky mountain rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill well.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together and cover with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° until casserole bubbles up.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Soften gelatin in small amount of V-8 juice.
Heat remainder of V-8 with herbs and other ingredients.
When sufficiently cool, mix in with gelatin and pour into a mold.
Serve with curried mayonnaise with olives to garnish.

title: nibblers
directions: Combine all cereal, nuts and pretzels in large baking pan. Melt margarine and bacon drippings.
Add all the spices and sauces.
Pour over cereal mixture and bake for 1 hour in a 250° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: baked seafood salad(great for leftover boiled shrimp!)
directions: In a 2 or 3-quart dish, saute butter, mushrooms, green peppers and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs and paprika.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and paprika.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix flour, oleo and cream cheese; refrigerate 1 hour.
In another bowl, mix 1 3/4 cups sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and butter.
Press into mini muffin pan from 1st mixture, about 1-inch dough to each cookie.
Put 1 tablespoon of brown sugar mixture per cookie.
Top each with crushed pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: zesty italian mini breadsticks
directions: Unroll breadsticks; do not separate.
Cut dough crosswise into 5 equal parts.
Separate into individual pieces.
In plastic bag, combine Parmesan cheese and seasoning.
Add dough pieces and shake to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 14 minutes until golden brown. Dip in spaghetti or pizza sauce.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate for 1 hour and serve.

title: spicy southern fried chicken
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Mix Bisquick, bread crumbs, chicken seasoning, salt and pepper in Ziploc bag.
Moisten and place chicken in bag and shake.
Heat oil and place chicken in oil.
Fry until brown.
Drain off grease.
Mix together barbeque sauce, honey, melted margarine, hot sauce.
Season to desired taste with salt, pepper and crushed peppers.
Pour a little in a small bowl with a sealed lid, place chicken in bowl, close lid and shake. Remove and put into serving dish.

title: caramel candy
directions: Put 1 cup sugar in pan over low heat until sugar melts.
Add hot milk, remaining sugar and corn syrup.
Cook until mixture reaches 238° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture is thick, but still shiny. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: apple chili sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a small pot for 45 minutes or until mixture thickens. Pour into hot, sterilized jar and seal.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Beat oil, eggs and sugar well; add vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture, apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nippy franks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except frankfurters in crock-pot. Slice frankfurters into 1/2-inch pieces and stir into sauce mixture. Cover and cook 1 hour.
Remove lid and heat an additional 2 to 3 hours.

title: frank's super welsh cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut into shortening (as for pie crust).
Drain currants and mix with batter; set aside.
Beat eggs light; add vanilla and milk.
Add flour to mixture and chill.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add apricots.
Add nuts.
Mix to coat apricots.
Add milk and eggs; blend well (do not have to beat).
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until brown, at 350°.

title: clara's oat raisin muffins
directions: Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Serve them for breakfast with a bowl of hash.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon onto waxed paper.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl, stir in oil, sugar, zucchini, lemon rind and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan or wire rack.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly.

title: heath candy-cookie bar
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum wrap.
Put a layer of saltine crackers on top of this.
Bring to a rolling boil, brown sugar and margarine; boil for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers; bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Pour a large bag of milk chocolate chips on top of this, spread until melted.
Top with nuts and refrigerate.
Break when cold and tear off aluminum wrap.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Remove fat from pork. Spray 12-inch nonstick skillet with cooking spray; heat over medium-high heat. Cook pork in skillet about 5 minutes, turning once until brown. Add broth, potatoes, carrots and onions to skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender and pork is slightly pink when cut near bone.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: hand lotion for face, hands, legs and feet
directions: Mix well and put in a pretty bottle.

title: quick squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except crackers, well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Bake at 350° until firm in the center.

title: 4th of july bean casserole
directions: In large skillet cook bacon, beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender, drain.
Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish and add beans, mix well.
In small bowl combine the remaining ingredients.
Stir into beef and bean mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Mix sour cream and seasonings.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture and place in buttered glass baking dish.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator overnight or at least 8 hours.
Sprinkle thoroughly with crushed stuffing mix.
Drizzle with
melted margarine.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Bake, uncovered, 15 more minutes or until meat is tender.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grate vegetables.
Combine with softened cream cheese, seasoning and mayonnaise.
Add more mayonnaise if necessary to make of spreading consistency.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spread on bite size pieces of bread or make small sandwiches.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
together
shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar. Mix
in
peanut
butter.
Add
well beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift
together flour, salt and soda and add to shortening mix. Mix
and
stir well.
Roll dough into small balls. Place on greased
cookie sheet. Crisscross with a fork.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: italian sausage green beans
directions: Wash and break green beans.
Place in a large saucepan. Remove casing from Italian sausage; break up and place in green beans.
Shake Bloody Mary mix and pour over green beans to almost cover beans.
Cook to desired tenderness.
Serve with Bloody Mary mixture in individual sauce dishes or drain as desired.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly add milk and vanilla. Pour into custard cups; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of hot water in 325° oven until mixture doesn't adhere to knife, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or chill and serve cold.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate and cheese cake layered dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter and nuts.
Press mixture into bottom of large glass Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add flour. Stir in chips and nuts. Shape into 1-inch balls. Flatten cookie with glass dipped in 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. While slightly warm, sift powdered sugar on top. Do not add salt to dough.....chips provide the salt.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into thick crosswise slices.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Coat tomatoes with dry mixture and drop into hot fat until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet n sour carrots
directions: Break egg in bowl. Add other ingredients and cook until thick. Pour over cooked carrots. (Adjust ingredients to fit amount of carrots and also to taste.)

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package.
Arrange cookie slices in bottom of a 15 x 10-inch baking dish.
Using floured fingers, press dough into pan to make a complete crust.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook meat with onion soup.
Put in crock-pot with mushroom soup and mushrooms all day.
One hour before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs until light, add sugar and flour.
Mix well, stir in milk, vanilla and butter.
Stir in coconut lightly.
Pour in 2 well buttered 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Forms its own crust.

title: danish puff coffee cake
directions: Measure first 1/2 cup flour into a bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup butter. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water. Mix with a fork. Form into a ball. Divide in half. Pat dough into 2 long strips (12 x 3-inches). Place on ungreased cookie sheets, 3-inches apart.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt cake pan, greased and floured lightly.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pistachio or any other pudding mix
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pecans and butter.
Crumble the butter into the flour; mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown; let cool.

title: baked beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Spoon into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving with crackers.

title: hot hamburger cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger with peppers and onions.
Drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce.
Return to heat and add tomatoes and diced cheese.
Heat over medium heat until cheese is melted and ingredients are mixed.
Simmer for an hour or so.
Keep hot in a crock-pot on low.

title: coconut balls
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in water. Add flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° about 20 minutes, or firm to touch.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.
Dip cookies in confectioners frosting and roll in tinted coconut.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: karen's quick raisin bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and raisins.
Add buttermilk and stir just until combined. Knead on floured surface for 30 seconds.
(Dough will remain sticky.)
Pat into 8-inch round.
Make "x" on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all other ingredients except pecans. Form into balls or log and roll in the pecans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Can use American cheese if you want.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine cake mix plus eggs and oil. You add raisins, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and 1/4 cup warm water.
Sift flour and soda. Mix with milk, shortening and yeast mixture.
Put in covered container.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Will keep for several days.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and butter together.
Place half of stuffing in pan.
Add carrot, squash, sour cream, soup, onion, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Place the rest of stuffing and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust and sprinkle with potatoes, then top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat 2 cups of water in a large pot until boiling.
Add vegetables; cover and cook until tender (about 10 minutes). Blend vegetables with part of the cooking water in a blender or food processor.
Heat olive oil in a small nonstick skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons of the 2 1/2 cups of water and then sprinkle in the flour.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Add the remaining water and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in broccoli mixture, instant chicken bouillon, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat just to boiling.
Stir in the evaporated milk and heat through without boiling again.

title: mexican dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sour cream together.
Put on bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish (oval or rectangular), then layer the peppers, tomatoes, olives and salsa.
Sprinkle cheese on top. It's delicious!!

title: moist and minty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup mint flavored semi-sweet chocolate morsels and vanilla extract, stirring until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth. Transfer to large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour mixture and remaining chocolate morsels.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, just until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut in 2 1/4-inch squares.

title: oven french toast
directions: Slice bread 1-inch thick and arrange in one layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients, except butter; beat together.
Pour over bread; dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
May refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
Uncover; bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pecan or coconut crispies
directions: Blend butter until soft.
Add brown sugar, 1 cup at a time. Beat eggs and add to sugar and butter.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together; mix well.
Add vanilla when mixed well.
Add coconut or pecans, divide mix and make both kinds.
Drop by spoon on pan.

title: salad dressing
directions: Pour juice into shaker top container.
Pour in enough oil to cover surface.
Add mustard.
Add garlic and spices (enough to cover surface).
Shake well.
Serve on tossed greens.
Serves 4.

title: spicy chicken and peppers
directions: Saute chicken breasts in 1 tablespoon olive oil until no longer pink.
Remove from pan; set aside.
Add 1/2 tablespoon olive oil and spices; mix together.
Add red peppers and onion; saute until onion is transparent.
Add the chicken and stewed tomatoes; simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Serve on split kaiser rolls.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in 9 x 12-inch well-greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown round steak in shortening.
Add onions, salt and pepper. Blend in flour, tomato juice and mushrooms.
Cover all.
Cook over low heat 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir in mixture of Pet milk and lemon juice.
Heat until steaming but do not boil. Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry pear compote(low calorie)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until berries pop and sauce thickens about 15 minutes stirring occasionally.
Serve warm or cold.

title: deluxe potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, add potatoes, onions and bouillon cubes. Cover with water.
Cook until tender. Add margarine, cheese, sour cream and bacon.
Heat until cheese melts. Add green onions.

title: mock duck
directions: Mix sage, pepper, salt, green pepper and onion.
Spread over steak.
Roll up, tie together and rub dry mustard over steak. Cook for 1 hour at 375° until tender.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight container.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer head of lettuce in oblong dish or bowl. Add celery, onion, green pepper, water chestnuts, frozen peas and carrots. Spread over all this mayonnaise. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: mushroom london broil grill
directions: Combine oil, sherry, pepper, celery salt, dry mustard and vinegar.
Pierce holes in steak with a fork.
Marinate steak and mixture in refrigerator overnight.

title: spicy beef and rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in a Dutch oven.
Add next 6 ingredients. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains about 94 milligrams sodium per serving.

title: christmas cheese balls
directions: Mix all together and roll in crushed nuts and place cherry on top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Peel and cut apples into chunks. In separate bowl, combine oats, butter, flour and spices. Grease an 8-inch square pan. Put apples in pan. Spread out oat mixture evenly over apples. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp; spread out in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan over low heat and pour over shrimp. Refrigerate, baste and turn shrimp every 30 minutes while refrigerated for several hours.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, turning shrimp at 10 minute intervals.
Serve in soup bowl with French bread to dip in sauce.

title: ice tea
directions: Combine water, sugar and tea bags and bring to a boil.
Let simmer about 5 minutes.
When cool, squeeze tea bags and remove from liquid.
Squeeze lemons into mixture.
Add orange juice to cooled tea.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Stir together margarine and milk in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add marshmallow and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together the first three ingredients, then mix the remaining ingredients in with the first three.
Pour into a greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: In medium bowl, cover mushrooms with hot water; soak 20 minutes, or until soft.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Remove and discard stems; slice caps into 1/4-inch thick strips; set aside.

title: cucumber and tomato salad
directions: In large pot, brown one pound of hamburger. When almost completely browned drain grease and add 2 diced onions.
Add 2 cans of diced tomatoes, 1 can tomato paste and 1 can tomato sauce. Stir until blended. Add oregano, basil, garlic salt or powder 3 times during cooking.
Add 2 green peppers and mushrooms.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix chopped onion, chopped tomato, chili powder and dried cilantro together.
Let sit.
In a blender, mix avocados and cream cheese until they are well blended.
Blend together.
Add garlic and seasoned salt to taste.
Put in bowl and chill 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Butter pan.
Place boned chicken in oblong pan.
Make layer of onion, half of chips and cheese, then other half of chips. Combine soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and broth.
Blend well.
Heat and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
In large bowl, to the mix, add oil and jello; blend well.
Add eggs and continue to blend for about 5 minutes.
Add extract and blend.
Pour in well oiled loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until well done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in casserole dish.
Top with sliced eggs and cheese.
Mix soup with milk and 1/2 of the onions.
Add this to casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
The last 5 minutes of baking, top with remaining onions.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together refried beans and taco seasoning.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan or Tupperware.
Spread all of sour cream on top of beans.
Spread diced onions and olives on top of sour cream.
(You can add other toppings here if you like).
Spread salsa on top of onions and olives.
Spread cheese on top of salsa.
Press cheese into salsa gently.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spoon into bowls and serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, molasses and vanilla. Mix flour, cinnamon, baking
soda
and
salt together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in
a
375° preheated oven 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: italian cabbage
directions: Saute onions in melted shortening.
Add cabbage and small amount of water.
Simmer until done to taste.
Add sauce and heat.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown hamburg, then drain it.
Mix beans, seasoning and sauce. Stir; mix well.
Put in bottom of pan.
Spread on sour cream. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: You will need 2 saucepans.
Combine chocolate pudding and milk in one pan and vanilla pudding and milk in other pan.
Cook over medium heat until they boil and thicken.
Stir peanut butter into vanilla pudding.
Drop warm pudding into crust, alternating chocolate and peanut butter.
Swirl together.
Chill completely. Serve with dollops of whipped cream.
Be sure you use 10-inch crust as this is a lot of filling.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook chicken in boiling water. After cooled, cut into bite size pieces.
Mix soups, chicken, onion, bell pepper and chili powder together in a bowl.
Soften tortillas and cut into bite size pieces (soften in microwave or in the broth the chicken was boiled in).
Put one layer of tortillas on bottom of casserole dish; then pour soup mixture over that. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pour full can of Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
This dish freezes well.

title: sunflower salad
directions: Line 2 plates with lettuce leaves.
Divide cottage cheese in half and scoop onto lettuce.
Arrange peaches around cottage cheese.
Cut cherry in half.
Place on cottage cheese.
Add celery stick for stem.
Serves 2.

title: hot corned beef mini-sandwiches
directions: Mash corned beef with fork; mix with other ingredients.
Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and line the loaves of bread across the length.
Carefully begin filling the sandwiches until all the mix is used.
(Be sure each sandwich has a top and bottom!)
Mix garlic powder to taste with margarine; spread lightly across the tops of loaves.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven.
Serve hot.
Can be covered with plastic wrap (vented) and microwaved.
Follow your oven's directions for heating breads.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and salt.
Stir well. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Stir quickly until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool for at least 2 hours.

title: pinto enchiladas
directions: Steam chopped vegetables in a small amount of water in a skillet.
Add the cooked rice, pinto beans, bean juice, garlic powder, salt and cumin.
Heat thoroughly.
Dip each tortilla in hot tomato sauce (see tomato sauce recipe) to soften.
Fill tortilla with 2 tablespoons of the rice-bean mixture.
Roll up and put into a 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Top with Cashew-Pimento Cheese Sauce (see recipe).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste occasionally during baking or cover with foil to prevent enchiladas from drying out.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with chips and/or crackers.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Place in a clear bowl and refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.

title: missouri dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and oleo until smooth.
Mix in sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Mix pudding, milk and vanilla together in a bowl.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Pour on cookies in pan.
Sprinkle rest of crushed cookies on top.
Chill and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, top with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit for 15 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Grease 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: Microwave pecans, sugar, Karo syrup and salt on High for 8 minutes.
Stir once after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add soda and stir until foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and cool.

title: mama's pepper biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
If dough is sticky, add more flour.
Knead until smooth.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk in quart pan.
Boil, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add oatmeal, vanilla and coconut.
Drop onto wax paper; let harden.

title: irish skillet bread
directions: Melt margarine plus 1 teaspoon salt in a 10-inch skillet. Combine flour, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and baking powder.
Blend eggs and milk in separate bowl; add margarine.
Combine with dry ingredients.
It makes a wet dough; add raisins.
Spread around in skillet; dust top with a little flour.
Score center of dough so it won't split.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cobbler (any kind)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl (mix by hand). Pour the mixture into a greased pan.
Place fruit on top of mixture until it is fully covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: roast beef
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and brown roast on all sides.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add coffee, 3/4 cup water, bouillon, basil, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover, simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Combine flour and remaining water until smooth. Stir into pan juices and cook until thick.

title: baked lasagna
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown ground beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, 2 cups water, salt and pepper; simmer 1 hour.
Meanwhile cook lasagna as directed on package.
Mix together eggs and Ricotta or cottage cheese.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1/2 cup sauce, then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce, Ricotta and egg mixture and Mozzarella until baking pan is filled.
Top with sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in moderate 375° oven about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn loaf
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Mix well and let sit for 30 minutes.
Combine eggs, milk and water.
Add to corn mixture. Thoroughly greased a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cocoa pudding
directions: Heat milk in double-boiler.
Add sugar, cornstarch and cocoa; cook until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and chill. Serve with whipped cream and nuts.
Good.

title: candy ice cream pie(easy!)
directions: Choose any flavor combinations:
caramel, hot fudge or butterscotch sauce; graham cracker or chocolate crust; vanilla, pistachio or chocolate pudding; toffee, Snickers or candied nuts! Make your own creation!

title: tangle britches(cinnamon pastry)
directions: Cream
together
the
butter
and sugar.
Add the eggs, beating well.
Sift in the cinnamon and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll	out the dough very thin on a floured board to about
1/8-inch
thick.
Cut
into rectangular pieces 3 x 5 inches.
Make
cuts
lengthwise in the dough 1/2 inch apart and 4
inches
long, so that the rectangle remains in one piece. Fry in hot deep fat (360°) for 2 minutes or until they bob up
to the top of the hot grease.	When dropping them into the fryer, pick
up the 1st, 3rd and 5th strips and pull them upward.	Let the
2nd,
4th
and
6th sag downward so that in frying they
get all fahuudelt (tangled) or as the Dutch say, all through
each other.
Dust with powdered sugar or dribble molasses over them and eat hot.

title: old time lemon meringue pie(club member: clint hudson)
directions: In saucepan, combine the 1 cup sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt. Stir in water. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and clear. Add a little hot mixture to egg yolks; return all to hot mixture. Cook 1 minute more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Blend in butter, lemon peel and juice. Pour mixture in baked shell. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add the 6 tablespoons sugar; beat to stiff peaks. Spread over hot filling. Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: bacon-scallion mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and garlic in a large pot with lightly salted water to cover 13 to 15 minutes until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley or nuts and shape into a ball.
Roll in parsley or nuts and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Keep covered.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans. Mix the sugar and cinnamon and roll each biscuit piece in this mixture. Layer in pan and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans and any leftover sugar. Melt the oleo and brown sugar and pour over bread. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pickled crab apples
directions: Wash apples.
Remove blossom end.
Do not pare.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add apples, a few at a time, and simmer until tender.
Pack apples in hot, sterilized jars, adding syrup to cover apples; seal.
These should be real sweet to be good.
Add more sugar, if too sour.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.

title: tortilla soup salad
directions: Combine jalapenos, olive oil, vinegar and salt.
Set aside.

title: pineapple coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with pineapple juice.
Stir in crushed pineapple. Turn into greased baking pan.
Combine rolled oats, brown sugar, cinnamon, melted butter, chopped walnuts and raisins.
Sprinkle over top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: skillet cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Melt butter; add beaten egg, sugar and dates.
Cook in skillet at 300° for 6 minutes and stir all the time.
Remove from stove. Add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups of boiling water over 2 cups all-bran, dates and nuts and let cool for 10 minutes.
Cream together the sugar, shortening, eggs and all-bran mixture.
Add buttermilk, flour, soda, salt and 4 cups all-bran.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Use as needed.
Keeps in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.

title: broccoli with sour cream sauce
directions: In double boiler, blend sour cream, soup, onion flakes, salt and cheese.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour hot blended sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle almonds and cheese crackers over all. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Let sherbet soften.
Put in punch bowl and pour liquids over sherbet.
Mix.
Makes 25 (6 ounce) servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl and mix together.
Pour ingredients into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Place tamales, cut into fourths, in a square or 9 x 4-inch rectangular pan, using the gravy, also.
Spread pork and beans over tamale layer.
Put chopped onion (according to taste) over the beans.
Spread chili over all for next layer.
Put layer of Fritos for top.
Bake at 425° until bubbly hot.
Serve with Fritos or saltine crackers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix Jiffy cornbread mix according to directions.
Add corn. Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Pour 1/3 of cornbread mix in greased pan or skillet, then layer hamburger, chopped onion, chopped peppers and cheese.
Pour rest of cornbread mix on top. Bake at 350° until done, about 50 minutes.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and let stand 10 minutes. Add to very warm water the shortening, sugar and salt.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Let stand 10 minutes, then work down 5 times 5 minutes apart.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each out flat and then roll like jelly roll.
Cut diagonally 4 or 5 times across top.
Put in French bread pan or on a cookie sheet and let stand to raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls (walnut size).
Cook in a 350 degree oven for 12-15 minutes. Makes about 85 balls.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Chop potatoes and eggs.
Crumble bacon and mix well with other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.
If desired, add grated cheese about 10 minutes before casserole is finished baking.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Beat with electric mixer until well mixed.
Add food color to desired tint. Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Use as many pork chops as wanted. Place in skillet and brown. Peel the potatoes and slice as thin as you can without breaking and place in casserole dish that has been sprayed. Put enough milk in to cover potatoes and place browned meat on top of potatoes. Season to taste. Bake until done. Be sure to cover.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place vegetables in kettle.
Sprinkle on salt. Place 5 trays of ice on top of vegetables.
Wait 3 to 4 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak cold from fridge into thin diagonal slices.
Melt butter in large skillet over high heat.
Add beef and green onion; sprinkle with salt.
Cook 3 minutes or until beef is done to your liking; remove and keep hot.
Add mushroom soup; slice mushrooms with liquid and wine to skillet.
Bring to boil, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir half cup hot liquid into sour cream in small bowl.
Blend into skillet; return beef to pan.
Heat 5 minutes.
Spoon over hot buttered noodles.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in oil, then zucchini and vanilla.
Stir together flour, nuts, cinnamon, allspice, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture, mixing only until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pans or 1 Bundt loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: mighty fine hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1 stick melted butter, onion, soup, sour cream, cheese and salt and pepper. Stir well and spoon into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Combine crushed corn flakes with 1/2 stick melted butter; stir, then sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup juice.
In a saucepan, bring water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and marshmallows. Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Toss bananas with lemon juice.
Fold bananas and pineapple into Jell-O.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine the sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Stir in egg and reserved pineapple juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oleo; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread over Jell-O. Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Combine margarine, vanilla and salt in a bowl and blend well. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add the flour.
Add chocolate chips and 3/4 cup nuts.
Mix well.
Press into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining walnuts over the top and press in lightly.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix together the pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: graham cracker delight(pie or cake)
directions: Mix graham crackers, white sugar, baking powder, walnuts and egg yolks together; then whip egg whites and fold in mixture.
Put in an ungreased pie pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash.
Crumble crackers and grate cheese.
Reserve 1/2 of the crackers and cheese for topping. Place squash, 1/2 of cheese, 1/2 of crackers, onion and other ingredients in a 3-quart casserole. Top with remaining cheese and crackers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream, blending well.
Spoon into crust; chill until set, about 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries if desired.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Save 1 cup of cake mix for topping.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain reserved marinade.
Grill 4 to 6 inches from medium coals.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with marinade.

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chopped potatoes, water, bouillon granules, ground red pepper and black pepper.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, cocoa and egg yolks until they are blended well; then add water and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture becomes thick enough to stick to a spoon remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell.
If you do not make meringue, a dollop of whipped topping is wonderful on this pie!

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables together.
Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, paprika and salt and pepper together.
Pour over veggies and let sit for 24 hours.
Will keep 3 weeks in fridge.

title: broccoli, chicken and rice casserole
directions: Dissolve dry onion soup mixture in chicken stock.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Place beef on the bottom of Pyrex dish.
Place the chicken breast on the beef.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream and water.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts.
Cook in a 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours, covered with Reynolds Wrap for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and continue to cook for the last hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt and baking soda together, then add egg and buttermilk.
Mix until right consistency to roll into balls.
Mix in one medium onion, chopped.
Roll into large or small balls and deep fry until brown and crispy (about 2 minutes).

title: french toast
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch slices.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients in blender and pour over bread.
Marinate in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
After 10 minutes, brush French toast with melted butter.
When finished cooking, French toast can be topped with cinnamon.

title: my best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar and softened oleo together.
Add eggs, salt, soda and vanilla, beating well.
Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Add the flour and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and cornstarch and mix. Add pineapple and cinnamon.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Do not cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well. Shape into small to medium balls. Place on cookie sheet and cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: perky tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix vegetables, eggs and pickles or celery with the cooked macaroni.
Then combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and Eagle Brand milk for the salad dressing.
Use only about half of salad dressing for macaroni and vegetables.
Mix salad thoroughly and keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: strawberry icing
directions: Crush strawberries with tablespoon of sugar and lemon juice. Gradually mix in confectioners sugar.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and shortening in saucepan.
Warm over low heat until shortening melts.
Set aside to cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water in a large bowl.
Add milk and 2 to 3 cups flour, beating to consistency of cake batter.
Let rise, covered, in warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Stir down and add salt, soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Beat in enough additional flour to make stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface. Shape into rolls.
Place in greased pans and brush with margarine. Let rise until doubled in bulk or refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: heavenly shrimp appetizers
directions: Place a cheese cube topped with a jalapeno in the "cradle" of each shrimp.
Wrap tightly with one bacon slice and secure with a toothpick.
Bake on a well greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve and enjoy!

title: tavern burgers
directions: Brown 4 pounds of hamburger meat and chopped onion (drain off excess fat).
Bring to a boil 1 can undiluted tomato soup, 4 tablespoons smoke sauce, 1 tablespoon vinegar, 1 tablespoon mustard and 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over meat and simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 15.

title: chicketti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and pepper. Combine taco sauce, soup, enchilada sauce and onion soup mix; set aside. In 9 x 13 baking dish, place a layer of tortillas, layer of meat and half of the soup mixture; repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover with Cheddar cheese and bake 15 more minutes. Use cake pan. Serves 6 or may do half recipe to serve 3.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: In bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish, combine croutons and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard and onion powder. Mix until blended.
Pour over crouton mixture in casserole.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Sprinkle over casserole. Set aside 1/4 for garnish.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes. Garnish with remaining bacon.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add meat and cook until tan.
Add onion, green pepper and other ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix and add butter, the size of a walnut.
Cook in heavy pan until thick.
Pour in a 9-inch baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Prepare and cook green beans, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oven to 350°.
Toss beans with oil, vinegar, onion, garlic and pepper.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and butter; sprinkle over beans.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple slices; reserve 2 tablespoons of syrup.
In pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add brown sugar; stir until sugar is melted.
Remove from heat. Arrange 8 pineapple slices on sugar mixture (1 in middle, others overlapping).
Put pecans in middle.
Halve remaining pineapple and arrange on edge; add pecans.

title: heartland onion soup
directions: Heat butter over medium heat in a soup pot until butter foams. Add the sliced onions; toss to coat completely.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until translucent.
Uncover pot; raise heat to medium.
Sprinkle onions with sugar, salt and thyme and saute very slowly until onions are a rich golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle browned onions with the flour; cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Ladle in the simmering beef broth, whisking to incorporate liquid.
Add the sherry and simmer soup 30 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and cook 10 minutes longer.
Season with black pepper to taste.

title: polish style stuffed eggs
directions: Chill hard-boiled eggs in cold water.
When completely cold, cut them in the shell lengthwise.
Take out the half egg carefully without damaging the shell.
Chop the egg.
Add a dash of salt and pepper, chopped chive or onion browned in butter and two tablespoons of sour cream.
Refill the shells; sprinkle the tops with bread crumbs and brown again, face down, in frying pan or butter the tops and brown under broiler.

title: harland sanders pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, Karo, sugar, salt, lemon juice, butter and vanilla.
Place pecan halves in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour in mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in 325° to 350° oven.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix above and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into large chunks.
Cook broccoli and cut into large pieces.
Mix all together; put in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Serve over wide egg noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in a large dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudgy mint squares
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, melt 8 tablespoons butter and unsweetened chocolate; cool slightly.
In mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs, sugar, and vanilla.
Add the chocolate mixture; mix until blended. Gradually beat in flour.
Spread into a greased 13x9 baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until top is set.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining butter.
Add cornstarch; beat until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk and remaining egg.
Add extract and food coloring if desired.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 15-20 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool on a wire rack.
In a heavy saucepan, combine chocolate chips and cream.
Cook and stir over medium heat until chips are melted. Cool for 30 minutes or until lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Cool for 2 hours or until set before cutting.
Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: diabetic vegetable soup
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings with 25 calories.
One vegetable exchange.

title: taco burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat and saute onions.
Drain.
Add catsup and seasoning mix according to directions on package.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: breakfast cheese cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 package of crescent rolls on bottom.
Beat until creamy the cream cheese, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and lemon juice.
Spread mixture on top of rolls; put 2nd package of rolls on top.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine, stirring in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in cake flour. Blend mixture until doughy texture.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pastas
directions: Cook and stir rosemary, sage, oregano, thyme and garlic in oil in a small saucepan over medium heat for about 1 minute.
Don't let herbs brown.
Add tomatoes and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine spinach, cheese and bread crumbs in medium bowl.
Fold in eggs.
Stuff the shells with the mixture of spinach.
Place 1/3 of tomato mixture on bottom of a 13 x 9 -inch pan.
Arrange shells in pan and pour mixture over shells.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheap and easy white icing
directions: Heat Karo until boiling.
Beat egg whites until stiff, salt added.
Pour boiling Karo over egg whites and beat.
Slowly fold in vanilla.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Saute the onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add mushrooms, shrimp and crab meat.
Cook until shrimp turn pink.
Add the mayonnaise, milk and rice to shrimp mixture.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, sprouts and apple in a bowl.
In second bowl, mix remaining ingredients and add to cabbage mixture.
Toss.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add liquid ingredients and mix well. Roll into 3/4-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in buttered casserole dish. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
On top put:

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: In a saucepan, cook brown sugar, flour and milk over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add a little hot mixture to egg.
Mix well.
Add egg to mixture and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Add bananas and peanuts alternately with pudding mixture.

title: egg rolls
directions: In wok, brown meat.
Chop all vegies in tiny pieces.
Saute vegies in 1/2 teaspoon oil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add cooked meat.
Add sauce.
Wrap in won ton paper.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: grandma's gelatin
directions: Mix jello, pudding and tapioca mixes with water.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and juice. Stir until mixed. Pour into mold, 9 x 13-inch pan or bowl. Chill until set.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Run cold water over cooked spaghetti to prevent sticking.
Cut vegetables into small bite-sized pieces. Mix spaghetti and vegetables together.
Prepare dressing mix and pour over spaghetti mixture.
Add Salad Supreme and mix.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup blueberries with sugar and water in saucepan. Mix cornstarch with a little of the water.
Stir to a smooth paste. Add to mixture in pan, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, lemon juice, jello and butter.
Cool.
Pour over remaining 3 cups (or more) blueberries in baked pie shell. Chill several hours.
We serve with Cool Whip.

title: rum bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking dish.
Place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rocky road bars
directions: In large bowl mix marshmallows and nuts.
Melt chocolate chips, condensed milk and oleo.
Pour over marshmallows and peanuts.
Mix very quickly.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Chill.

title: potpourri of sherried fruit
directions: Use any variety of fruit that you like.
Drain fruit, place in shallow casserole.
Add dry sherry and let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter. Place in oven at 350° until thoroughly heated (about 30 minutes). Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serve in decorative bowl.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a large bowl arrange in layers the onion, tomatoes, cheese and beans (which have been drained and lightly rinsed).
Next add the lettuce and pour dressing over all.
Place bowl in refrigerator and chill for 1 hour.
Then lightly crush Fritos, adding and tossing well just before serving.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 5 minutes on medium.
Mix well and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 1/4 cups of condensed milk for your favorite pies.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and roll out onto floured surface.
Cut biscuit size pieces out.
Roll each biscuit out thin and put pie filling in center.
Fold over and use water to seal edges.
Fry in hot crisco until brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper in a frypan.
Set aside and let drain.
Mix soup, water and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add rice and simmer seven minutes.
Add sausage mixture; mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover and put in oven.
Bake at 375° for thirty-five minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top (optional).

title: rice with black beans
directions: Cook and stir onion in hot oil until tender but not browned. Add tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Return to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients, including liquids from all cans.
Simmer and serve with a sprinkle of Cheddar cheese and tortilla chips.
(I cook in the slow cooker.)

title: baked crusty pineapple for 50
directions: Place pineapple slices in shallow pan.
Cream sugar, butter and spices and put on pineapple slices.
Pour juice over and around pineapple.
Bake for 25 minutes in moderate oven.
Let cool and serve one pineapple slice topped with large spoonful of ice cream to each person.

title: franks and spaghetti
directions: Saute frankfurters, onion and green pepper in butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and cumin; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add olives.

title: chip dip
directions: Fry the hamburger and drain.
Add the cheeses, soup, water, sour cream and salsa.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water until crunchy.
Place broccoli in
10 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Add chicken and cover with cheese.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice. Pour over broccoli and cheese.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fat free pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until tender.
Wash in cold water and drain.
Mix pasta with the rest of the ingredients and serve or refrigerate.

title: tuna rice salad valenciana
directions: Combine rice, tuna, celery, olives, pickles and seasonings. Toss lightly.
Combine mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice; pour over salad.
Gently blend.
Spoon over salad greens and garnish with capers and additional sliced olives.
(Tasty substitutes for tuna:
chicken, shrimp or crabmeat.)

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix milk, eggs and mix.
Add oil and ice cream. Bake in a 375° oven.

title: heavenly brownies(foolproof; family recipe)
directions: Grease pan.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peach slices in an 8-inch square pan.
Cream margarine and 3/4 cup sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon mixture over fruit. Sift together remaining 1 cup sugar, nutmeg and cornstarch; sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: frozen cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Mix thoroughly the pineapple, cranberry sauce, sour cream and pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and freeze 3 hours or more.
Thirty minutes before serving, remove from freezer and place in refrigerator.

title: baked haddock
directions: Dip haddock in egg then roll both sides in the cracker crumbs.
Place in a baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Dot with butter and bake at 500 degrees for about 12 minutes.

title: zucchini-chive biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in shredded zucchini, milk and chives until just combined.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and water.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over butter, then spoon the fruit all around over the crust.
Put a few small pats of butter on top.
Crust will rise to top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: saucepan spaghetti
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown ground beef on medium heat; drain fat.
Add the water, tomato sauce, onion, oregano, basil, salt, garlic powder and pepper into the pan and stir.
Cook on high until the mixture is bubbly.
Break the spaghetti in half and add it to the saucepan mixture.
Cover and simmer on low for 30 minutes or until the spaghetti is tender.
Stir often with a wooden spoon.
Serve hot with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in water; coat with seasoned flour.
Put in baking dish.
Dot with oleo.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix water and powdered milk.
Pour over chicken and continue to bake 45 minutes more.

title: pollo encaldo chicken soup
directions: In a large pot brown cooked rice in 1 tablespoon butter, then add canned tomatoes and boiled and deboned chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes.
In another pan brown cubed pork meat and vegetables. After browning, add to rice and chicken mixture.
Add vermicelli and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add water as needed.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In baking pan, brown ribs on both sides.
In a saucepan add butter.
Cook onion until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook slowly until flavors are blended, about 10 to 15 minutes, then pour sauce over browned ribs.
Cover tightly and bake in oven (350°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: layered puppy chow mix
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given into a wide-mouth 1-quart canning jar. Pack each layer in place before adding the next ingredient.

title: chocolate orange torte
directions: Spray a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Set aside.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Place in casserole dish in layers (two) 1/2 of margarine and onions, 1 can beans and 1/2 can soup. For second layer, last 1/2 onions and margarine, 1 can beans and last 1/2 can soup.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes. Pull out of oven and sprinkle on buttered bread crumbs.
Place back in oven for about 5 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
In a medium bowl, combine the artichokes, cheese, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Spoon the artichoke mixture into two (1 cup) ramekins. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbling. Serve as a dip with corn chips.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, cheese, Rotel tomatoes in pan over low heat.
Mix 1/4 sauce with with cut-up cooked chicken over low heat.
Cook tortillas in butter. Fill tortillas with chicken mixture and put in baking pan.
Pour remaining mixture on top of tortillas.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: macaroni and cheese and corn casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Strain through sieve.
Butter your dish and then put 1 layer of macaroni, 1 layer of corn and 1 layer of cheese. Repeat this until almost full. Then on top put bacon strips and then bake in oven until bacon is brown.
Serve hot.

title: judge alice's pot roast
directions: Rub the roast with pepper.
In a large heavy pot, heat the olive oil and sear the roast on both sides until well browned. Pour in the wine and add the parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in the onions, carrots, potatoes, tomatoes and celery.
The liquid should not cover the meat completely.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: fruit medley
directions: In a bowl, combine pie filling, pineapple, oranges, cherries and bananas. Cover and refrigerate. Just before serving, stir in pecans. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Marinate cubes of lamb, chicken (boneless breast or boneless thighs) or beef at least overnight, the longer the better!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter. Mix with cornbread dressing. Put 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly. Place chicken on top of dressing. Mix sour cream and soup; spread over chicken.
Add sage. Pour 1 can chicken broth over all. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wild rice and chicken bake
directions: Place uncooked rice and half the flavor packet (about 1 1/2 tablespoons) in a 3-quart rectangular baking dish.
