Stir in water, soup, water chestnuts, frozen peas and carrots.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes, until chicken and rice are tender. Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Use remaining seasoning another time with rice.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zesty "fried" chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine cornmeal, paprika, salt, garlic powder, pepper and cumin.
Rinse chicken (do not pat dry); coat chicken evenly on all sides with cornmeal mixture.
Spray a large skillet and cook chicken for 8 to 10 minutes until no longer pink, turning occasionally to brown on all sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cubed potato salad
directions: In large bowl add cubed potatoes, pimentos, eggs, pickles and onions.

Add pickle juice, sugar, salt and paprika to suit taste. Add salad dressing and fold ingredients together until well mixed. Do not stir too vigorously as it will break down potato cubes. Remember, this is cubed potato salad.

title: ham ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayo.
Stir in next 4 ingredients. Cover.
Chill several hours.
Form into ball and roll in nuts.

title: beef or chicken enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in and out of oil (or broth) to soften; drain on paper towel.
Dip tortillas in Enchilada Sauce.
Place cheese and onion in center.
Roll up and place in baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and grated cheese.
Heat at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Place water, pineapple or orange juice, dates and raisins into blender bowl and blend until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and mix lightly.
Scoop onto lightly sprayed Pam cookie sheet with spoon or small ice cream scoop.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.
Let cool.
Ready to serve.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and chill (all day).
Next add the rest of the ingredients.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplants in half lengthwise and steam until less then tender.
Lay bay leaf and whole clove over eggplants in steamer and throw out bay and garlic when finished steaming.
Cool eggplants until you can remove seeds.
Scoop out some of meat (don't break skin).
Put meat in bowl and chop well.
Add tomato, bread crumbs and spices.
Cook all of this in 1 tablespoon of hot oil.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti or macaroni in chicken broth.
Saute in butter the celery and green pepper.
Add mushroom soup, milk and cheese. Warm until cheese is melted.
Layer spaghetti, meat and sauce. Bake until bubbly at 350° in large casserole.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Cook until done and add taco mix or peppers.
Mix corn bread mix according to directions.
Add corn.
In an 8 x 8 x 12-inch greased pan, pour 1/2 corn bread mixture, then all of the meat.
Grate cheese over the meat and add remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate overdose cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Fold in fudge and chocolate morsels and mix.
Roll into golf ball size balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut roll mix into quarters and roll into balls.
Shake dough balls in mixture of 3/4 cups sugar and cinnamon.
Layer dough balls around a greased tube pan.
After all are layered, boil butter or margarine with 1 cup sugar, pour over top of cake. Preheat oven to 350° and bake cake for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine Mix, baking soda, cream of tartar and egg.
Mix well.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small dish.
Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mix and place 2-inches apart on unbuttered baking sheets. Flatten balls slightly.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned with cracked tops.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: cavatina
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Brown beef and drain.
Brown pepperoni. Mix first 4 ingredients together and add spaghetti sauce.
Layer in a baking pan 1/2 pasta, 1/2 meat sauce, all of cottage cheese, 1/2 mozzarella, remaining pasta, remaining meat sauce, and remaining mozzarella.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 -35 minutes.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Season chicken with Accent and let stand.
Empty apricot preserves in large mixing bowl; refill preserve jar with French dressing and add to preserves.
Empty 3/4 of the onion soup mix and mix thoroughly.
Dip the chicken parts in glaze mixture; arrange on baking dish.
Pour the remaining glaze mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle the remaining onion soup mix over the chicken. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave creamed corn
directions: Mix corn and water.
Cook on High 10 minutes.
Add more water if needed and stir.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Cook 10 minutes or until thickened.

title: susan bars
directions: Beat together all ingredients except chocolate bits and walnuts.
Spread in ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
While baking, melt chocolate bits in small saucepan.
Spread melted chocolate bits over bars while warm.
Sprinkle crushed walnuts over melted chocolate bits while warm.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: susan's easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef in 3-quart saucepan and drain fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lasagne, for filling.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagne over sauce.
Cover with about 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 of cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagne, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagne and remaining sauce.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Have
about the same amount of broccoli and cauliflower. Mix all
ingredients.
Sprinkle with 1 package of Good Seasons Italian dressing.
Sprinkle over top of vegetables as it comes in
the package.
Don't mix.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning,
pour
large
bottle
of
Zesty Italian dressing
over vegetables.
Add juice from half a lemon.
Toss and
serve.
Can add tomatoes before serving (optional).
Will keep well in refrigerator several days.

title: pork loin with sweet potatoes and parsnips
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large frying pan, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper and cook until well browned on all sides, about 8 minutes.

title: george govier's favorite dessert(chocolate sundae)
directions: Fill bowl with a generous serving of vanilla ice cream. Completely cover ice cream with chocolate syrup.
(If you can see the ice cream, you need more chocolate syrup.)

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Heat milk in large saucepan until simmering.
Cook broccoli and onion in milk until tender.
Melt butter in small saucepan; stir in flour.
Add butter flour mixture to milk.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cheese and salt.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle fried onions on top.
Bake until onions get brown.
Serves 4.

title: *cranberry bread
directions: Add boiling water to shortening to make 3/4 cup.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Add egg and juice and mix again.
Add cranberries and nuts and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour in 325° oven in a greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: *One cup nonfat plain yogurt and 1 cup nonfat or low-fat cottage cheese, mixed, but not food processed!

title: spanokopita(greek spinach cheese pie)
directions: Wash spinach, drain and chop.
Cover and cook with just water that clings to the leaves until tender, about 3 minutes.
Drain. Mix spinach, cheeses, onion, parsley, dill weed and salt; stir into eggs.
Brush bottom and sides of oblong baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch) with softened margarine.
Unfold filo leaves.
Remove 10 leaves.
Cut crosswise into halves.
Cover completely with damp towel to prevent drying.
Wrap and refreeze remaining filo leaves. Gently separate 1 leaf.
Place in baking dish, folding edges over to fit bottom of dish.
Brush lightly with melted margarine. Repeat 9 times.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spread spinach-egg mixture evenly over filo leaves.
Layer 10 more filo leaves over filling, spreading each leaf with margarine and tucking in around edges to cover.
Cut pastry through top layer of filo with sharp knife into 6 squares.
Bake, uncovered, about 35 minutes until golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Mix Jiffy as directed on box.
Put on top and bake until corn mix is done at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning in bowl. Spread on dish evenly.
Spread small amount of salsa on top. Layer lettuce (chopped), layer tomato (chopped) and layer shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a pan.
Mix oleo with 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and oleo for 10 minutes (this is a must).
Spread on crust.
Slice bananas over mixture; apply pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip and spread over fruits.
Add chopped nuts and cherries to top.
You may use coconut too.

title: toffee squares
directions: Beat until light and fluffy the butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add the dry ingredients.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix bacon, cheese and onion.
Spread on each slice of bread that has been flattened and had edges cut off.
Cut bread in half. Place asparagus tip on each half.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in 13-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 30 rolls.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes; spoon into dessert dishes or cut into squares and invert on dessert plates.
Top with ice cream and spoon sauce over each serving.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
In large bowl, mix hot water, 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs, salt, vanilla and dried milk.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix in enough flour to be able to handle dough.
Set in warm place to raise until double in bulk.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, water and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and apples. Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: stove top play dough(for kids)
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Add water, coloring and oil.
Cook and stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes. When it forms a ball, turn out and knead on lightly floured surface.
Store in airtight container.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients except brown sugar and bacon fat (oil) into a sauce pan.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add in the brown sugar and bacon fat (oil).
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: martha craver's chicken and dressing
directions: Cook a whole hen in right much salted water.
Pour chicken broth over broken bread and crackers.
Soak until completely wet. Stir lightly.
Stir in beaten eggs and seasonings.
Place whole chicken in a deep earthen dish, breast side up.
Pour dressing around hen.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles per directions on box and drain when finished.
In pan used for cooking noodles, mix egg with milk and return noodles to pan and thoroughly mix noodles into egg/milk sauce.
Coat sides and bottom of 8 x 12-inch casserole pan with Pam or product of choice to prevent casserole from sticking to pan while cooking and place noodle mix in pan, spreading evenly over pan bottom.

title: charcoal quail
directions: Marinate quail in oil for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Cook over hot charcoal for 20 to 30 minutes, basting with Charcoal Bird Sauce.
To serve, pour remaining sauce over quail.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl and mix well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake for another 35 to 40 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, water, cornstarch and syrup and boil until clear.
Remove from heat.
While still hot, add package of jello. Stir well.
Let cool but don't let it jell.
Add strawberries and stir gently to coat each one.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Cook meat, onion, chili powder, salt and pepper until done. Mix milk, soup and green chilies together.
Start with tortillas on the bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan. Layer tortillas, meat mixture and soup mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes or until it is hot through and through.

title: baked chicken with sherry-mushroom sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Mix soup, mushrooms with liquid and remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake until chicken is hot and sauce is bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well (except frosting).
Batter will be thin.
Bake in 4 layers or 2 layers and split when baked and cooled.
Watch carefully if cake is baked in 4 layers, it will burn easily.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes for 2 layers and 15 minutes for 4 layers.
Frost with Butterfinger Frosting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Saute onion and pepper, add hamburger, tomatoes and soup; mix well.
Cook macaroni; drain and add to hamburger mixture.
Put 1/2 of hamburger in casserole dish. Put 4 slices of cheese on top.
Add other half of hamburger mixture.
Put rest of cheese on top.
Put in 350° preheated oven. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: beth's favorite pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil pepperoni for 5 minutes.
Drain. Set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter for 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Pour remaining butter into an 8-inch baking pan and toss with cooked spaghetti.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Peel apples; remove core.
Make syrup of sugar, water and red drops by boiling for 5 minutes.
Add apples; cook until tender.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut squares of aluminum foil approximately 12-inches square. Slice a potato, a carrot and onion and dab with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Top the vegetables with a hamburger patty, a minute steak or a pork chop.
Wrap up.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for about 1 hour.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together. Put in greased Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or slightly brown on top.
Great with crackers.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade, condensed milk and Cool Whip; stir until lemonade is dissolved.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Chill at least 8 hours.

title: brunch pie
directions: Mix hash and 1 beaten egg; press into 1 (9-inch) pie plate, buttered,
to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Layer cheese, onion and vegetables in crust.
Beat together remaining 2 eggs, milk, flour, mustard, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour mixture in crust.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, until filling is set. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Put into dish.
Pour chicken soup over this.
Add rice and top with mushroom soup.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: skilletburgers
directions: Brown beef; add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Spoon onto toasted hamburger buns.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add sugar, pineapple and pecans.
Blend.
Add cranberries.
Fold cream into cheese mixture and freeze.
May be kept for weeks in the freezer.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together a day ahead of serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix, then sprinkle with cheese and Ritz crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin spread
directions: Mix and serve with gingersnaps.

title: no cook karo frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add sugar (1 tablespoon at a time), beating until smooth and glossy.
Continue beating and add Karo syrup, a little at a time, beating after each addition until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
Frosts 2 pies or 2 (9-inch) layer cakes.

title: tropical waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples and bananas.
Sprinkle with orange juice and toss lightly.
Add other ingredients.
Stir in enough either mayonnaise or salad dressing to moisten.
Serve on lettuce. Serves 6.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Cook chicken; let cool and cut into pieces.
Heat soup, milk and cheese in saucepan over low heat.
Cook until cheese melts. Place chicken in big end of crescent roll and roll up.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until rolls are browned and cooked through.

title: mexican cheese melt
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion and season with salt and Tabasco.
In baking dish, spread beans and top with meat mixture.
Add green chili.
Cover evenly with cheese.
Drizzle with taco sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and garnish with olives and green onion.
Serve with tortilla chips.
May also be served as a casserole.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Combine milk and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups of sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened (about 30 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla flavoring.
Pour into 10-inch round baking dish.
Layer with pineapple and vanilla wafers.
In bowl, add pinch of salt to egg whites.
Beat until peak forms.
Spread over top of pudding.
Bake at 350° until egg whites are browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles. Cook ground beef until brown, Drain well. Add taco seasoning with a little water and mix well. In 13 x 9 baking dish, layer lasagna noodles, meat, salsa, and cheese. Repeat ending with cheese. Bake at 350° until melted through.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Cream together until fluffy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup hot milk while beating with electric mixer until smooth and stands in peaks.
Use 3 tablespoons cherry juice for cherry frosting or 1 tablespoon maple flavoring for maple frosting.
Maple is good on a butter pecan cake mix.

title: sugarless coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell as directed.
Combine milk, flour, egg yolks and NutraSweet.
Cook in top of double boiler in skillet with water until thick.
Add coconut, vanilla and margarine.
Put in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
Add some NutraSweet.
(I put about 1 teaspoon of marshmallow cream to egg whites.)
Put over pie filling.
Sprinkle coconut on top of meringue.
Bake until golden brown, at about 350°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except kisses in large bowl.
Mix until dough forms ball.
Shape into balls, using rounded teaspoonful for each (roll in hand).
Roll balls in granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around the edge.
Let set for at least 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup boiling salted water.
While that is cooking, saute onions in oleo.
Add soup and simmer about 3 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Add broccoli and rice.
Bake in a buttered casserole 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: mock lobster salad
directions: Crumble crackers; add remaining ingredients and mix.
Crackers should be in large pieces.

title: king ranch hamburger casserole
directions: Line 9 x 12 pan with tortillas. Place meat, onion, cheese, chili powder, garlic powder and tomatoes in layers. Mix together the soups (no water) and spread over the top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: light and fluffy pound cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl; cream until light.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl.
Add flour mixture to butter, alternating with milk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan (or two loaf pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or until knife inserted in center comes out clean).
Cool completely and remove from pan.
Delicious alone or with strawberries and whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix together the eggs, oil, sugar and apples.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add walnuts and raisins. Batter is thick and makes a large 13 x 9-inch cake.
Grease pan and pour batter in.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
You may serve with whipped cream.

title: almost fat-free zucchini bread
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together.
Mix all the wet together, then add zucchini.
Spray a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with mixer; add sugar and salt until dissolved.
Stir in corn syrup and melted butter; mix well.
Stir in pecans and pour into pie shell.
Make cover for pie by rolling square of foil around edges to form round tent to cover pie. Secure under lip of pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from pie and bake 15 minutes longer or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Add flour slowly while beating mixture.
Add salt and baking powder, then lemon and vanilla flavor.
Mix very well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275° or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into meat balls (each approximately 2 inches in diameter).
Cover bottom of skillet with cooking oil. Fry meat balls until a light brown color, not crusty.
Makes approximately 12 medium size meat balls.
Set aside to finish cooking in spaghetti sauce.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Add pudding mix to Cool Whip in a large bowl. Add other ingredients and stir well.

title: smothered round steak
directions: Brown steak in small amount of cooking oil in large skillet. When brown, set steak aside and then brown onion, pepper and celery.
Cut steaks into serving portions and add to cooking pot with 3 to 5 cups boiling water, then add other ingredients and seasonings.
Cover and simmer on low heat for about 2 1/2 hours. Add enough water to keep steak covered if necessary.
Juice may be used as gravy.

title: camper's cookies
directions: Combine first five ingredients in saucepan.
Boil one minute. Add last three ingredients.
Stir and drop quickly from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: german chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Combine ingredients all together.
Blend well.
Drop by rounded teaspoons into bowl of sugar.
Gently toss.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce for 50
directions: Put cranberries, apples and orange peel through food chopper (coarse knife).
Cut oranges in small sections with scissors; add sugar.
Stir well and set in icebox.
Will keep several days. This is nice to serve as a sauce, congealed as a salad, adding 2 cups of pecans or served in little parfait glasses as a dessert. Halve this for a small family.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip; pour into a graham pie crust.

title: favorite zucchini squash
directions: Wash zucchini and boil whole just until done, about 10 minutes.
Cut off ends and cut in half lengthwise.
Arrange in buttered casserole.
Melt butter and mix in cheese and sour cream. Add salt, paprika and chives.
Pour over squash and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: toasted herb rice
directions: Measure rice into oven-proof casserole with lid.
Place into 325° oven.
Roast 20 minutes or until rice is toasted and golden. Remove from oven.
Add margarine to rice and stir until melted. Pour boiling broth and water over rice; stir.
Cover.
Return to oven.
Bake 30 minutes or until rice is done and has absorbed all liquid.
Stir in finely chopped green onions, soy sauce and herb of your choice.
Makes 4 servings.
Good served with baked or roasted chicken or beef.

title: crunchy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar and margarine until well blended.
Blend in egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop tablespoonsful of mixture on foil covered cookie sheet.
Start testing it after 12 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes. Makes approximately 15 cookies.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until stiff. Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts and chips.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased, foil-covered cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cookies in oven and turn heat off immediately.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.

title: mom's cherry slice cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add juice, flour and baking powder.
Add nuts and chopped cherries.
Spoon on cookie sheet and shape into 6 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make buttercream frosting and add 2 drops food coloring for color.
Slice loaves.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquid until very warm (120°).
Add to dry mixture and beat well. Stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) pans which have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in uncovered dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Cool to set.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with the nuts and coconut.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Take 4 slices of bread; cut off the crusts.
Roll out each slice until thin; lightly butter.
Place an asparagus spear on end of slice; roll up tightly.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place on plate and garnish.
Use for party plate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, add slightly thawed strawberries, pineapple (juice and all).
Let stand a while, add the bananas, mashed.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate.
When firm, spread sour cream over top.
Then put other half of jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Refrigerate until firm.
Sweet enough to serve as dessert.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes. Cut in half and scoop out the middle.
Mix onion, butter and sour cream with the scooped out potatoes.
Beat until mixed.
(Similar to mashed but not as smooth.) Spoon bake into shells and place Cheddar cheese on top. Put in microwave or oven to melt cheese.
(Can use French onion dip in place of sour cream if desired.)

title: layered salad
directions: Place in 9 x 13-inch pan in order in layers.
Mix 2 cups mayonnaise with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Spread over the top; sprinkle with 4 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: wesleyan rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 375°, uncovered.

title: "company's comin!" green salad
directions: In a very large salad bowl, mix all ingredients lightly.
Pour dressing over all; mix lightly again.
Refrigerate.
This salad is better if made the day before and is good for several days.
A good make ahead dish.

title: peach stuff
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and coconut real well.
Put in margarine and cut in until lumpy.
Dump into floured pan.
Pat with spoon.
Put in preheated oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take peaches (drained).
Put in 3 rows. Sprinkle mix of cinnamon and sugar over whole pan.
Mix egg yellow and sour cream; pour over middle of 3 rows of peaches.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until eggs are done.

title: italian beef
directions: Boil roast with first 3 ingredients until tender.
Take meat out of broth and cool.
Discard onions.
Slice beef very thin. Cover with broth; bring to a boil and add the next 6 ingredients to this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on Italian rolls.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in a container with a lid.
For each cup of cocoa, use 2/3 cup hot water and 1/4 cup cocoa mix.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay 3 strips of bacon on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until bacon is brown.

title: brownies
directions: In small mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan (double batch takes a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan).
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cocoa, oil, flour mixture, then nuts last.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° until top has dull crust and pulls away from pan slightly, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares (or 32 for larger pan).

title: chinese casserole(chicken or turkey)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Toss lightly; spoon into buttered 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through, bubbly and brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Place tidbits in baking dish; top with shredded cheese.
Mix with juice, 3 tablespoons of flour and sugar.
Pour over cheese and pineapple.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika.
Beat all together; pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cookies(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar, eggs and bananas.
To this mixture, add the flour, oatmeal, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla; blend well.
You may add nuts or raisins, if you like. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 9
by 13
by 2 inch dish; add chicken, vegetables and soup. Mix well together and set aside. In a small mixing bowl mix flour and milk together. Pour over first mixture. Bake at
350° until crust in done and is golden brown color. About 20 to 30 minutes. Can also use fresh skinless, boneless chicken breast instead of canned chicken.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, melt margarine in microwave.
(Use a large saucepan for stove top melting.)
Add cocoa and mix.
Add sugar and beat with mixer.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flour and mix.
Cook in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover pan tightly with foil while still hot.

title: summertime salad
directions: Blend juice into cheese.
Fold in pecans, pineapple and cherries.
Mix Dream Whip and stir into mixture.
Chill.

title: holiday sugar roll cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in egg and flavoring.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours or roll immediately. Cut in any shape.
Bake at 325° until done, but not brown. Decorate or frost when cool.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all together and stir-fry with baby carrots, broccoli, tofu, pea pods, cellophane noodles, ginger and mushrooms (stir-fry separately first, not in sauce, these take too long).
A great lo-cal dinner choice!

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Blend in flour and sugar.
Pour into freezer container and add milk to the fill line markings on container.
Freeze according to your ice cream freezer directions.

title: chicken rice skillet dinner
directions: Melt margarine and cook the chicken in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add carrots and green onions; cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally so that the chicken doesn't stick to the bottom.
Add soup and milk; cook for about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add rice and mix thoroughly.
Take the pot off the burner and let it sit for 5 minutes, until mixture is absorbed by rice.
Serves 4.

title: crackle-top molasses cookies
directions: These cookies come out crackled like a gingersnap!

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter; add evaporated milk a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and powdered sugar.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans in hot water; drain.
Combine in large kettle with ham hock and 4 quarts hot water.
Cover.
Cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours or until beans are tender, but not mushy.

title: oyster stew
directions: Bring 1 cup of the oyster liquor to a boil and when it has cooked for 5 minutes, skim off the top, which will be foamy.
Add the cream, butter and seasonings to taste.
Cook the oysters in the other cup of liquor until the edges curl (about 5 minutes). Strain and add to the cream.
Serve immediately.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onions in pan.
Cook macaroni as directed on box until almost done while meat and onion brown.
Drain macaroni and add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour fat off ground beef.
Add to the drained macaroni.
Stir well and let simmer on low heat for about 30 minutes.
(You may want to add more tomatoes or medium can of juice if you want to be more juicier.)
This is good served with tossed green salad and French bread.

title: anna rogers' homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix and knead about 3 minutes.
The dough should be stiff and more flour may be needed.
Roll very thin on floured board, taking care not to let dough stick to the board.
Let stand 8 to 10 minutes to dry.
Turn dough and let stand 8 to 10 minutes longer. Roll up loosely like a jelly roll and cut across to make long strips 1/8-inch wide.
Unwind strips and again let stand until dry.
What is not used can be frozen until needed.
It is nice to have a package frozen to use for emergency.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and chopped celery; drain fat.
Add tomato juice, kidney beans, chili powder, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: chocolate oat chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat softened oleo and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips, flour and nuts.
Mix well; drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in water.
Knead until smooth.
Extra flour if needed.
Divide in 3 sections.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut in squares and drop into boiled chicken.
Cook until done.

title: greek eggplant dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake slitted eggplant in shallow baking dish until soft, about 50 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and garlic and saute until transparent.
Set aside.
Remove eggplant and cool.
Peel off skin and take out seeds.
Place eggplant pulp, onion and garlic into food processor and puree.
Add salt, cumin, pepper, yogurt and lemon juice.
Puree.
Chill.
Add chopped tomato and garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve on warm pita bread triangles.
Makes 4 cups.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Beat until foamy.
Serve warm.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine water, sugar and cinnamon in saucepan, bringing to a boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Chill.
Then combine sugar and syrup with remaining liquids.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 3 3/4-quarts.

title: green beans deluxe
directions: Fry bacon and reserve drippings; set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings in skillet until tender.
Blend flour with sugar, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, salt and mustard in large saucepan.
Stir in tomatoes and sauteed vegetables.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over green beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend 10 seconds at a time, for 3 or 4 times. Pour into buttered and floured 10 inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix with mixer, eggs, sugar, Crisco, anise and milk.
Mix dry ingredients and combine with egg mixture.
Grease cookie sheets. Roll into balls and place on sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Frost with confectioners sugar and milk.
Sprinkle with candies.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel tomato and finely chop. Combine all ingredients. Cover tightly and chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onions and peppers.
Shape into 6 patties.
In a large skillet over medium heat, cook patties until brown on both sides. Spoon off all fat.
Stir in remaining soup and the fresh mushrooms; add salt and pepper.
Return patties to skillet and reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until done, turning patties occasionally (about 20 minutes).

title: microwave jelly
directions: Place frozen fruit in 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave on Full Power for 2 minutes or until thawed.
Stir in powdered fruit pectin.
Cook in microwave on Full Power for 2 minutes or until few bubbles surface.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Cook on Full Power for 6 minutes.
Stir 2 to 3 times during cooking time.
Pour into glass jars.
Cover and refrigerate.
If sealed with paraffin, jars may be stored in freezer for use when needed.

title: hot hominy
directions: Fry sausage and crumble or brown like ground
meat.
Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and simmer 20 minutes.
In buttered casserole dish, alternate layers of hominy mixture and cheese, ending with cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook pepper in salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Brown beef in skillet.
Add all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Stuff peppers and place in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: almond crackers
directions: Mix butter and sugar to a cream; pour in the milk, slowly, then add flour.
With palm of hand, pat out the mixture on buttered tins (cookie sheets) as thin as possible; cover with blanched almonds.
Bake in moderate oven, 335°, for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking powder with milk.
Melt butter in baking pan.
Spread flour mixture in pan.
Pour fruit over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned.
Serves 6.

title: cheese lasagna
directions: Mix cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Layer noodles in baking dish. Add cheese mixture (noodles, cheese, noodles, cheese and noodles).
Drizzle melted butter on top and sprinkle with parsley. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove for the last 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spread chicken in oblong baking dish; spread vegetables and corn over chicken, then layer the soups and broth over all ingredients.
Mix flour with milk until thin; pour over and bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: french chocolate ice cream
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil; boil rapidly for 3 minutes.
Put chocolate chips and hot syrup in blender.
Cover and blend on high for about 10 seconds, or until smooth.
Add egg yolks; cover and blend 5 seconds.
Fold chocolate mixture in whipped cream.
Spoon into refrigerator trays or individual serving dishes, and freeze 2 to 3 hours.
This ice cream remains creamy without stirring.

title: lo-cal buttermilk dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together all ingredients.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: honey chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts.
Combine mustard, honey, garlic and soy sauce until smooth and pour over sauteed chicken breasts and heat through.

title: five-star brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until well mixed. Add butter and shortening. Combine flour, cocoa and salt; stir into egg mixture and mix well. Add nuts, if desired. Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil and grease the foil. Pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brownies test done with wooden pick. Cool in pan. Turn brownies out of pan onto a cookie sheet; remove foil. Place a wire rack over brownies; turn over and remove cookie sheet. Cut with a star cutter or into bars. Yield: about 3 dozen.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs and milk.
Blend.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in very hot oven of 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until mixture doesn't adhere to knife.

title: lena's bean soup
directions: Cook all together until meat is well done.

title: cauliflower saute
directions: Arrange cauliflower in steamer basket.
Place over boiling water.
Cover and steam for 8 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: hoagie sandwiches
directions: Brown beef and sausage together in skillet; drain fat from meat.
Stir in half of pizza sauce.
Spread remaining pizza sauce on open buns; top with meat mixture and then sprinkle with cheese. Place in heated oven set on broil until cheese bubbles.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 open faced sandwiches.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add pork.
Stir-fry until well browned.
Add peppers.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, cornstarch, garlic powder, ginger and pineapple chunks in juice.
Add to the skillet.
Bring to a boil. Cook rice.
Serve pork mixture over rice.

title: low-fat tuna casserole
directions: Cook green onions in oil until tender.
Stir in water, rice, green pepper, carrots, bouillon granules and thyme.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir tuna and tomato into rice mixture.
Cover and simmer 10 more minutes or until tuna is heated through.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Gradually add dry ingredients to wet mixture.
Lastly, add carrots.
Pour into 12 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix together the enchilada sauce, chicken soup, mushroom soup and milk.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer.
Start with spoonful of sauce, then chips, then sauce, then cheese.
Make 3 layers of each:
chips, sauce and cheese.
Finish with chips (breaking chips in smaller pieces).
Best made a day ahead.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°, or until hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cake
directions: Shred fruit peels.
Halve cherries.
Chop nut meats and dates. Cut pineapple and citron.
Dredge fruit in 1/4 cup of flour. Cream the shortening with sugar.
Add honey.
Add beaten eggs; beat until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour (which has been sifted with all dry ingredients), alternately with fruit juice.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour batter over fruits and nuts; mix well.

title: debbie's tasty tacos
directions: Layer 1/4 cup of pinto beans, 1 tablespoon cheese, 1/4 cup lettuce and 1/4 cup tomato pieces in each taco.
You can top with sour cream, grated cheese, taco sauce or avocado.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Trim fat from lamb; rinse and dry.
Make slits in lamb with knife; insert garlic.
Sprinkle oregano, pepper and lemon juice. Put in a 9 x 12-inch roasting pan.
Turn lamb after 1 1/2 hours in a 375° oven.
If desired, roast potatoes.
Remove lamb.
Add potatoes and water to juices in pan; return to oven for 1 hour, or until done.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add sifted flour mixture and bananas alternating.
Add 1/4 cup buttermilk and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy(good smooth recipe)
directions: Put sugar, milk and margarine in a kettle.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes, continuing to stir.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat until cool.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool; cut into desired size pieces.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients except oils and seed in processor. Process until combined, about 15 seconds.
With motor running, add oil through feed tube slowly.
Add seed; turn on and off 2 to 3 times.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: coffee punch
directions: Make very strong coffee.
Cool and add sugar and vanilla.
Mix in bourbon and pour into a punch bowl.
Add ice cream and stir. Put the whipped cream on the top.
Serve.
Yield:
24 cups.

title: * easy mexican cornbread *
directions: According to package directions, prepare cornbread.
Spread mixture in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread sour cream evenly over top and dot with chilies.
Bake according to package directions.

title: cheesy cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over mix and bake at 350° until golden brown.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Slice onions into rings and put in 9 x 13-inch shallow pan. Top with apple pie filling.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover all with barbecue sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and cook for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream loaf cake
directions: Sift the flour, add baking soda, salt, and baking powder. Sift again. Cream butter, add sugar gradually.
Beat until light & fluffy.
Add eggs & blend well.
Add flour alternately with milk & cream.
Beat until smooth, add vanilla.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven 325° for 30 min.

title: microwave italian-seasoned chicken
directions: In a large strainer, rinse vegetables with warm water to thaw slightly.
Place vegetables in a 1 3/4-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry.
Fold chicken pieces in half; secure with wooden toothpicks.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture, coating generously.
Arrange chicken pieces with the thickest portions toward the edge of the casserole. Sprinkle chicken with paprika and any remaining crumbs.
Cover and cook on 100% power for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Makes 4 servings, 285 calories.

title: danish meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix meat.
Soak bread crumbs in milk; add, then add eggs, onion and flour together.
Mix all with hand. Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture appears light and frothy. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Form a loaf of the mixture in a baking dish.
Put the bacon on top.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours. Baste several times during baking with the juice or stock.
Slice thinly when cool.

title: hershey candy bar cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each one.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, nuts, melted candy bars and syrup.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan. Remove from pan and frost with candy icing when completely cool.

title: fresh veggie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place crosswise in ungreased baking pan.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Blend sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spread over crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and enjoy.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter until cooked.
Add cubed pieces of chicken; season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and wine.
Cover and let cook for 15 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and ketchup.
Dissolve all-purpose flour in 1 cup of water.
Add to chicken, stirring until thickened.
Stir in sliced mushrooms. Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in whipping cream.
Serve with rice.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add 1 cup broth, pepper, bay leaves, cloves and thyme.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: granny's norwegian egg cakes
directions: In blender, beat eggs, sugar and milk.
Mix dry ingredients together and add a little at a time to egg mixture, using blender on low. Use either 10 or 8 inch skillet, depending on what size you want the pancakes.
Smaller might be better until you get the hang of it.
Pour about 1/2 cup mixture in pan sprayed with cooking spray. Swirl around pan and watch constantly.
Work edges and peek underneath to see if browned, it will only take 30 seconds or so. Turn with flat wooden stick or wide spatula.
Cook on other side about 15 seconds and take out of pan.
Don't get discouraged, it takes a couple of times to get the hang of it.
Serve with butter, a little sugar and maple syrup.
Good with strawberries and a little maple sugar.
Serve with sausage for breakfast or supper. They are kind of like crepes, but thicker and better, of course. The Norwegians take the credit for this.

title: cocktail dip
directions: Place cream cheese on plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Serve with corn chips or raw vegetables.

title: meat noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat.
Add onions, celery and green pepper; cook until tender.
Season.
Alternate meat and noodles in greased casserole.
Pour over soup, mixed with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: italian flat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and honey in warm water and set aside.
Mix flours, 1 tablespoon oil and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Knead for 10 minutes or 10 seconds in food processor.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour (until double in bulk).
Punch down and let rest 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed. Pour 1/2 mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt oleo and caramels.
Mix well with Eagle Brand.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over cake. Pour caramel mixture on.
Pour on remaining cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked indian pudding
directions: Scald 3 cups milk.
Mix the egg, molasses, 1 cup cold milk and cornmeal into remaining ingredients. Add to the scalded milk and cook over hot water until thick.
Pour into baking dish and bake in slow oven (approximately 325° to 350°) for 2 hours.
Serve with cream or hard sauce.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in salted water until tender.
Add milk, margarine, pepper and flour thickening.
Simmer 20 minutes. Cheese may be added if desired.

title: party mints
directions: In mixing bowl, combine syrup, butter and extract; mix well. Add sugar, a little at a time, stirring until well blended.
Add food coloring.
Roll in small ball; flatten with fork.
Let dry for 3 hours.
You may also use candy molds to shape candy.

title: yeast biscuits (shortcake)
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water, yeast and honey and let bubble in small bowl.
Mix together flours, cashew meal and salt in large bowl. When yeast mixture bubbles, pour into flour mixture.
Add 4 cups hot water.
Mix just enough to moisten flour.
The dough will be very sticky.
Let rise about 1/2 hour.
Pour out on a generously floured board.
With hands floured, work in 1/4 to 1/2 cup flour. Pat out 1 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Wipe any excess flour off biscuits.
Place on "Pammed" baking sheets.
Let rise again.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Biscuits freeze well. Reheat and serve.
For shortcake, thaw and heat as needed throughout peach or berry season.
Makes 40 biscuits.

title: southern sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except for the butter and marshmallows.
Make sure to blend well.
Turn into buttered, medium-deep baking dish and dot with butter generously.
Bake in 400° oven about 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and put back in oven for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: sesame cookies(italian)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Beat in vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and beat well.
(Dough should be stiff.)
If necessary, add 2 more tablespoons of flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Divide into quarters and roll out (roll in the sesame seed) on floured board.
(Roll as rope 1/2-inch diameter, cut in pieces about 1 to 2-inches long.)
Bake 15 minutes until golden.
Enjoy.

title: chinese noodle cookies
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Take off heat and add noodles and nuts.
Drop on waxed paper.
Refrigerate after cooled.

title: boiled pot pie
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Cut in shortening until fine.
Beat egg in measuring cup.
Add enough water to make a cup of liquid.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well to moisten.
Turn out on floured board and knead about 10 times.
Roll until about 1/4-inch thick. Add flour to rolling pin and surface as needed.
Cut in 1-inch squares and drop into boiling broth.
Takes about 20 minutes to reach chewy texture that is pot pie.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar.
Beat egg.
Add shortening and milk with yeast, sugar and egg.
Add flour.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Make dough into rolls.
Place rolls onto greased pan.
Let stand 2 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with melted butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the soup, cheese, eggs and mayonnaise together. Fold in broccoli and pour in casserole dish. Cover with just enough crushed Cheez-Its on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Stir 1/4 cup mix into one cup
of hot water.

title: dill pickles
directions: Cider vinegar, water and pickling spice is enough for approximately 6 quarts of dills.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter in bowl.
Press over bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cream confectioners sugar, 1/2 cup butter and cream cheese in mixer bowl until fluffy.
Blend in egg. Spread in prepared dish.

title: pork chop sauce
directions: Brown the pork chops with the onion.
In a separate bowl, combine the catsup, Worcestershire sauce and cream of chicken soup. Stir and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: margaret's famous chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box.
Mix all ingredients for icing and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 minutes after mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Cool to lukewarm and beat until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts coarsely.
Put into baking dish.
Add Parmesan cheese, mayo, garlic powder and Tabasco.
Mix together well and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Pour into hollowed out bread loaf and serve with bread or crackers.

title: harvard red beets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beets and butter.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add beets and butter.
Cook a few minutes longer.

title: elephant stew(serves 3,800)
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Reserve the trunk; you will need something to put the pieces in.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook on stove for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve about 3,800 people. If more are excepted, the 2 rabbits may be added.
Do this only if necessary as most people do not like to find a "hare" in their stew.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Combine reserved juice and sugar, stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour pineapple juice mixture over salad. Toss and chill for 1 hour.

title: cheese bread braids
directions: Combine 3 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, butter and salt just until warm (115° to 120°) and butter is almost melted, stirring constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs and cheese. Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes on high speed.
Using a spoon, stir in as much flour as you can.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes).
Divide into thirds. Form each portion into a ball.
Wrap in clear plastic wrap; transfer to freezer bags.
Seal, label and freeze.

title: chicken-broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix and place in casserole.
Top with shredded almonds and grated cheese.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas, beating well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven about 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap; store at least 1 day before slicing.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil for 1 minute while stirring constantly.
Pour over graham crackers, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix thoroughly, then press with hands in a 9-inch square pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: frozen strawberry fruit pie
directions: Break frozen strawberries into chunks in mixing bowl; add sugar, egg whites and lemon juice.
Beat at highest speed with electric mixer for 15 minutes or until stiff.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust; freeze.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: butter tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Line muffin tins with a rich pastry.
Fill only 2/3 full with above filling.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: flaked goulash
directions: Brown turkey; drain off liquid.
Mix all ingredients together. Simmer until juice thickens, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: piccalilli
directions: Cut enough tomatoes in quarters to make 8 cups (if large cut into eighths).
Put 1 cup vinegar and 1/4 of tomatoes with blender, cover and blender chop (or put all vegetables through a grinder with medium fine blade, pour veggies into large kettle and add 4 cups vinegar).
Repeat with 1/4 of tomatoes and one cup vinegar if this method is used, until 4 cups vinegar has been used and all tomatoes chopped.
Cut peppers into eighths; remove membrane and seeds, peel onions and cut into sixths.
Blend chopped peppers and onions with water and drain.
Add to tomatoes.
Over high heat, heat veggie mixture to boiling, reduce heat to medium and boil, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring often.
Drain veggies and discard liquid.
Into drained veggies stir in remaining 2 cups vinegar and the rest of the ingredients.
Heat on high to boiling, reduce to medium heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, soak bread in milk for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix gently.
Shape into loaf and place on rack in pan.
Spray rack and pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Combine egg yolks and remaining ingredients; beat smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Chill; pour into glasses.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg if desired. Makes 8 (6 ounce) servings.

title: orange pancakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, orange rind and orange juice.
Add pancake mix.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter onto preheated skillet at 375° and bake until bubbles break and edges are cooked.
Turn and bake on other side.
Serve immediately with orange sauce.
Makes 24 (4-inch) cakes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add flour, eggs and chocolate syrup.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding until thickened.
Add sour cream.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mixture alternately with vanilla wafer and bananas.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients together. Add gradually to milk. Add chopped nuts and prunes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground chuck; drain off grease, then add taco seasoning mix and prepare according to instructions on taco mix. Set aside and let cool. Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and green onions and place in large bowl. Rinse and drain pinto beans, then place in large bowl. Then add all other ingredients and toss. Do not add ground chuck, taco chips, Green Goddess dressing, Cheddar cheese and taco sauce until right before serving.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake in three cake pans (floured and greased) until golden brown in a 350° oven for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ranada's spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour tomatoes and tomato sauce in large saucepan.
Add chopped peppers, onions and sliced mushrooms and olives.
Add ground beef (precooked) and press garlic in to taste.
Add all other spices gradually until to your liking.
(I use 2 to 3 tablespoons of all.)
Cook on medium for 10 to 15 minutes, then let simmer for 30 minutes or more.
The longer it cooks, the thicker and more flavorful it will be.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add all ingredients except 1 cup of pecans.
Mix well and roll in a ball.
Roll ball in the remaining pecans to coat.

title: veal stew
directions: Brown veal cubes in a Dutch oven pot or large pot.
Set aside. Saute carrots, celery and onions.
Add crushed garlic.
Return meat to the pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover pot and simmer for one hour.
Stir occasionally.
In the last 20 minutes, prepare rice in another pan.
Serve stew over rice.

title: apple roll
directions: Lay pie crust over 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Fill with apples. Fold crust over apples, making a roll.
Boil together brown sugar, water, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
Pour over roll and bake in 350° oven until brown and crispy, about 1 hour.
Baste some while baking.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased pan until done at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: nine day cole slaw
directions: Combine chopped cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Add 1 cup sugar and blend well.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and allow to cool.
Cover and store in refrigerator for at least 1 day before serving.
Stays fresh and crisp for 9 days.

title: stuffed white squash
directions: Place squash in a pie plate; add water.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes; rearranging after 2 minutes.
Remove from dish and set aside.
Place butter in pie plate and microwave at High 50 seconds.
Stir in onion and green pepper; microwave at High 2 minutes.
Combine sauteed vegetable, egg and next 3 ingredients.
Set aside. Remove a slice from stem end of each squash.
Scoop out and discard pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Spoon stuffing mixture into shells; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place squash in pie plate and microwave, uncovered, at High 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield: 2 to 4 servings.

title: chicken breast in sour cream gravy
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and sprinkle with lots of paprika.
Top with butter patties and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove chicken and make gravy in drippings with the mushroom soup and sour cream. Top with onion rings and bake 20 minutes or more.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika in paper or plastic bag. Brush chicken with lemon juice.
Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time to bag and shake well to coat chicken with flour mixture. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Stir in green onion, brown sugar, lemon peel and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Cover; reduce heat.
Cook over low heat for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Scramble hamburger and onions, drain excess fat.
Add salt, pepper, spices, tomato puree and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes. In large pan of boiling water, drop lasagna noodles in and cook until first limber, not done.
In large, deep baking dish, put a layer of meat sauce, noodles, then Mozzarella, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese, repeat ending with Mozzarella and Parmesan on top.
Bake at 325° until slightly brown.

title: butter pecan turtle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cover with 1 cup pecans.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute the butter and brown sugar.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Spread milk chocolate chips and let melt.
Spread to frost.

title: gold water beans
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off grease. Add to cooked beans.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Smash artichoke hearts and mix with cheese and mayonnaise. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: my sugar free banana nut ice cream(delicious, but not low calorie)
directions: Cook pudding according to directions.
When finished cooking, add condensed milk. Stir together and pour into freezer container. Carefully fry nuts in butter until just beginning to turn golden brown.
Do not burn.
Add nuts and mashed bananas along with other ingredients to pudding/canned milk mixture.
Add enough milk to reach fill line.
Add NutraSweet to taste.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: cold linguini
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix salad dressing and Salad Supreme with noodles.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add tomatoes and olives.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes; chill 2 hours.
Add celery and onion.
Chop egg white; add to potatoes.
Sieve yolks; mix with mayo, sour cream and horseradish mustard.
Fold into potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and celery seed to taste.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: apple puffed pancake
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, flour, white sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish in oven.
Add apple, return to oven until butter sizzles, not browns.
Remove dish and pour batter over apples; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes until puffed and brown.
Serves 6.

title: mocha drop cookies
directions: Beat oleo, egg, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add soda, salt, coffee and flour; mix.
Then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350°.
When cookies are cooled, ice with white icing and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: mother's old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, blend margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Put by teaspoon on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper. Flatten with a fork to 2-inches (will spread when baked to 4-inches).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet and remove to cooling rack.
Sift confectioners sugar over tops.
Yields 3 dozen large cookies.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Deep fry (or bake on a rack in a roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour).
If deep frying, cook for about 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy.
Drain.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Simmer the raisins in a small amount of water 15 minutes. Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients except pie shell.
Pour blended ingredients into shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 20 minutes longer until set.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add sour cream, onion and dried beef.
Top with pecans and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Boil and blanch rice.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (can make 2 smaller dishes and freeze one).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12. Dish can be frozen after it is baked.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten 2 packages crescent rolls on large pizza or jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool.
Beat together with mixer until smooth the softened cream cheese, salad dressing and dry Ranch.
Spread on cooled crust.
Add fresh vegetables of choice on top.
Such as:
broccoli, cauliflower, fresh sliced mushrooms, chopped green pepper, chopped tomatoes and sliced radishes.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top, cover and refrigerate.

title: cashew cake
directions: Bake in bundt cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Combine four, salt, soda, baking powder together then mix with other ingredients then add vanilla and chopped nuts; stir.
Add 2 cups of cashew.

title: ken's fat-free salad dressing
directions: Stir together and pour over salad.

title: cheese ball no. 2
directions: Finely chop onions and olives.	Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form
into
ball
and
chill
at least 2 hours. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Beat in a large mixer bowl 3 minutes. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer slaw
directions: Stir mustard into salad dressing.
Add cream and vinegar. Toss onion and caraway seed with chilled cabbage.
Add only enough dressing to moisten, then toss.
Pass remaining dressing with walking sandwich.
Makes 6 servings as a sandwich topper or 4 to 5 servings as a salad.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Heat water and butter to a rolling boil in a 2-quart saucepan. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by scant 1/4 cup onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Form into finger shapes.
Bake until puffed and golden.
Make pudding.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam.
Line bottom of dish with cherries, then pour layer of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix and pour on nuts.
Last, put cut up margarine on top.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 325°.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, salt and vanilla; blend well.
Add sugar and dry ingredients.
Mix well, then fold in apples and nuts by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch or tube pan, greased and floured, 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: short cut guacamole
directions: Place beans in food processor and chop until chunky. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: fried onions and green tomatoes
directions: Melt shortening; saute onions over medium heat for 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes; saute for 5 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: graham toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange crackers in single layer in ungreased pan.
Heat sugar and butter to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over crackers. Spread evenly. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake until bubbly, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly. Cut into bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine in large bowl.
(Mix with electric mixer) until melted; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and cocoa (don't sift flour); add soda.
Will foam a bit when soda is added.
This can be baked in an oblong pan (greased and floured) or tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Will be a heavy cake.
Frost with your favorite.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: micro rice pudding
directions: Beat egg.
Add ingredients except vanilla.
Cook in microwave Medium to High for 15 minutes, stirring ever 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pudding will be runny, thickens as it sets.

title: chili
directions: Brown slowly together the ground beef and onions. Add salt and pepper to taste, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pistachio ambrosia
directions: Drain canned fruits; reserving 3 cups juice.
Set fruit aside; pour juice into a 4 quart bowl.
Add pudding mix and mix until smooth.
Stir in sour cream; add whipped topping and mix until smooth.
Fold in fruit; chill for several hours.
Top with pecans just before serving if desired.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: upside-down meat loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 3 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Press the sugar in bottom of pan and spread the ketchup over the sugar.
Mix the remaining ingredients and shape into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn upside down to serve.

title: cole slaw(serves 50)
directions: Grate cabbage, onion and carrots.
Mix mayo, salad oil, vinegar and sugar together and pour over vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp relish
directions: Combine shrimp, onion and parsley in large bowl.
Mix salad oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Pour over shrimp.
Marinate several hours.
Heap shrimp in serving dish. Makes about 25 to 30 servings.

title: cracker dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add the beef; stir.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar together until smooth. Add the egg yolk and mix in thoroughly.
Sift the flour; measure and sift again with the cinnamon.
Add flour to the creamed mixture using your hands to blend together lightly but thoroughly.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured cake pan (9-inch round or 8-inch square) 20-25 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat chicken salad
directions: In large pot of boiling water, add the 3 bouillon cubes. Allow to dissolve.
Drop in chicken breasts.
Turn burner down to just below medium heat.
Cook for 1 hour.
Remove chicken from water.
Place in covered bowl.
Allow to cool in refrigerator. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise dressing in separate small bowl. Chop chicken breasts in medium size pieces.
In large bowl, add chicken, celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream and mayonnaise mixture until everything is well coated.
Ready to serve.
Can store in refrigerator for up to 3 days.

title: feathery fudge cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy (beat 5 minutes at high speed on mixer, scraping bowl occasionally to guide butter into beaters or beat 5 minutes by hand).
Blend in chocolate.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with ice water.
Beat after each addition.
Bake in two paper-lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Frost cooled cake with Chocolate Satin Frosting.

title: champagne delight
directions: Follow directions on Jiffy mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan not very long.
Beat until fluffy the pudding, milk and cream cheese. Spread on top of cooled cake.
Put drained pineapple on and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: mom's special chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat into slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes until brown and delicious.
Cool and enjoy!

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in butter.
Cook rice.
Place all ingredients except cheese in a 3-quart saucepan; mix well.
Cook on top of stove over low heat 1 hour.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: my sister linda's beef barley soup
directions: Add above to broth.
Cook 1 hour.
When almost done, add 6 shakes of thyme powder.
Then add the shredded meat.

title: mexican salad dressing
directions: Beat ingredients together with mixer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple date bars
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oatmeal.
Add margarine and mix well.
Add baking soda which has been dissolved in the water.
Mix well and spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread on filling and crumble rest of batter over filling.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.
Cut into bars while hot.

title: cornmeal cereal
directions: Toast almonds
in oven until light brown.
Boil 1 quart of water.
Mix
pint
plus 1 1/4 cups cold water with cornmeal. Slowly
add cornmeal to boiling water.
Stir constantly for 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. Makes approximately 1 1/2 quarts.

title: lori's breakfast pizza
directions: Place pizza in refrigerator as soon as you get home from Pizza Hut.
The next morning, take the pizza out of the fridge and place in microwave.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds to 1 minute. Remove pizza from microwave and bon appetit!

title: hot beef or venison sandwiches
directions: Roast ingredients at 300° for five hours; may also cook overnight in a crock-pot.
Tear or cut roast apart.
Add 1/2 bottle of prepared barbecue sauce.
Heat well and serve on buns.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Start by layering these ingredients as they are listed on large serving platter with raised edge or lip.
Chill 6 to 8 hours (overnight) and serve with scoop size Fritos.
tags: mashed ripe avocado with lemon juice

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars, egg and remaining ingredients.
Arrange by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with sugared fork.
Bake until firm, approximately 10 minutes.

title: tommy's mints
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar, cream and peppermint extract; mix well.
Mold into desired shape and place on wax paper to dry.
Store in refrigerator.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs, 2 sticks oleo and vanilla. Add flour and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Blend in nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a greased 11 x 16-inch pan.

title: grandma's caramel corn
