directions: In a 1 1/2 quart saucepan combine: brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt if using.
Cook to boil, them reduce heat and cook 15 minutes.
Add in baking soda and vanilla.

title: ribbon fantasy fudge
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling for 4 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add 1 cup (1/2 jar) Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, beat until well blended.
Spread evenly into greased pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate pieces.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.
A 1-ounce pieces has 139 calories.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender. Add currants.
Mix eggs and milk together and add to flour and fruit mixture.
Dough will be stiff.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Divide dough in thirds.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on pastry cloth.
Cut with circular cookie cutter.
Grease griddle lightly or you may use electric fry pan.
Heat to 350° to 375°.
Bake slowly, few at a time.
When done on 1 side, they will turn shiny and puff up. Turn and bake until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack and dip in granulated sugar.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: shredded wheat cheese dreams
directions: Split Shredded Wheat biscuits and spread with butter.
Mix cheese and mustard.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into cheese mixture.
Spread on halves of Shredded Wheat and place in a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° until puffed and slightly browned.
Makes 12 dreams.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then stir all until crumbly.
Make into small balls. Bake on greased pan 15 minutes at 350°.
Flatten the balls with the bottom of a glass greased with butter and dipped in sugar.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute cut-up sausage.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour egg mix on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: russian tea concentrate
directions: Add tea, cloves and cinnamon stick to boiling water. Steep for 15 minutes.
In another pan, boil 3 cups water with sugar. Add juices. Refrigerate.
To serve, dilute with equal amount of water and heat.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake in oven at 350° until brown.

title: june's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat in egg.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla or almond extract.
Chill if dough is too soft for easy rolling.
Roll out on a well floured board fairly thick.
Cut into desired shapes. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned on the bottom.
Cool and frost with any vanilla icing.

title: stuff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain oil.
Add meat to cooked macaroni. Mix in soup and milk.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add Ranch Style beans and heat; also add paprika.
Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place Doritos along edges and crunch on bottom to cover.
Next pour on half of the Ranch Style beans and meat mixture, crunch a few Doritos and put half the grated cheese on top.
Repeat with the balance.
Finally, pour soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes (heated together previously) over entire mixture.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: turkey pie
directions: Spread turkey in bottom of baking dish.
Mix together cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Pour over turkey.
Add vegetables; mix well flour, margarine, baking powder and milk. Pour this mixture over turkey.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta apricot salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water for 10 to 20 minutes or as package directs.
Drain and let cool (you'll get about 2 cups pasta). Combine pasta, apricots, chicken, zucchini, red pepper and basil in bowl.
Pour Fresh Apricot-Basil Dressing over.
Toss gently. Serves 4.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Let cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended.
Stir in flour, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan or on wire rack.
Cut into pieces.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat together.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour over beef and serve on hamburger buns, etc.
Tastes even better on second day.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and beef, breaking up beef with spoon; cook, stirring often until meat loses its red color, about 4 minutes.
Stir in half of the Cheddar cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt, basil and pepper.
Reserve.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine rhubarb pieces, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour. Place in 8 x 8-inch baking pan and dot with butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb (mixture will be crumbly).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or with topping.

title: spoon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
You can spoon onto lettuce and top with fruit.
Really good.

title: cowboy cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Can use light cream cheese if desired.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In small bowl, whisk seasoning packet from noodles and remaining ingredients except the noodles.
Pour oil mixture over cabbage; stir until coated.
Crush Ramen noodles and stir into cabbage.
Serve immediately.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in bowl.
Top with dressing and bacon bits.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler. Add milk slowly.
Stir and cook over boiling water until it boils. Add beaten eggs and butter and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and coconut.
Cool and pour into a cooked pastry shell.
Spread with meringue.

title: ocean garden spaghetti
directions: Drain tuna.
Lightly saute onion, garlic, broccoli, mushrooms and oregano in oil and butter.
Add zucchini and tomatoes until tender-crisp; break up tuna and add to vegetables.
Stir in sour cream to make sauce.
Toss with spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well. Add dry ingredients. Mix and then add nuts.
Bake in 1 pound coffee cans filled half full for 1 hour at 350° or use bread pans.
Do not grease cans or pans.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: hot meat potato salad
directions: Cook meat, onion, bell pepper and pimentos in butter until meat is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve at once.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Cut into small pieces.
Pour chicken broth and soups into saucepan and mix well over heat. Sprinkle part of stuffing mix in greased casserole dish.
Place chicken over mixture.
Pour part of soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with the rest of stuffing mix.
Pour balance of soup over casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Rinse caps in a pan of cold water.
Remove and let drain on paper toweling.

title: raisin cake
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over raisins and boil 15 minutes. Take from stove and let cool, then add 1 cup cold water.
Add remaining ingredients, raisins and water.
Mix well.
Grease cake pan and pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Place both in
double boiler and stir constantly.
This must heat slowly.
Use tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice enough apples to use in pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar with flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Line pie pan with crust, then put a layer of apples into bottom of pan.
Sprinkle some of the sugar mixture over apples.
Continue layering apples and sugar mixture until crust is full, ending with sugar mixture.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover with top crust and crimp edges.
Brush with milk and sprinkle some sugar over top crust.
Make some slits through top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Salt, pepper and tenderize them. Roll in bread crumbs and brown in 3 tablespoons olive oil.
When pork chops are brown on both sides, remove from skillet and place in an ovenproof casserole pan.
Slice onion in 1/4-inch slices and place a slice on each pork chop.
Seed and wash pepper pod.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices and put on top of onion slices.
Pour the rice over chops.

title: sausage breakfast dish
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix sausage with rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with pineapple and juice.
Cut the fresh pineapple in half.
Scoop out and use this for a bowl to serve dip in.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cream and boil to soft ball stage, 236°.
Then beat until mixture begins to sugar.
Add nuts and drop on greased waxed paper into 2-inch patties.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Makes about 24.

title: cranberry apple ade
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: beef texas skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and chips.
Don't drain beans or tomatoes.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes covered, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese to melt.
Remove from heat. Serve with chips.

title: polish bigos
directions: Cut up the sauerkraut, add a small amount of boiling water and simmer until tender.
Shred the fresh cabbage and cook in the same way, with the mushrooms added.
In a hot skillet, brown the pork on all sides in a little fat.
Add to the sauerkraut together with the bacon and simmer, covered, until meat is tender.
Render the salt pork, add crisp pieces to the sauerkraut, and use the pork fat for cooking onion until lightly browned.
Add the flour, stirring to prevent lumping, and cook until that browns.

title: piney punch
directions: In large saucepan, prepare cranberry-apple juice according to label directions.
Add cloves, lemon and cinnamon; bring to boil. Boil gently for 10 minutes.
Remove and discard spices.
Serve warm.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.
Serves 12.
Contains per serving: 0 grams fat and 38 calories.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Fill saucepan large enough to cook macaroni with water and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook for 7 minutes.
Put strainer in sink and drain macaroni.
Rinse with cold water.
Melt 4 tablespoons of the butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour and blend into smooth paste.
Add dry mustard and blend. Slowly add milk and stir.
Bring milk to simmer; it will begin to thicken.
Season with salt.
Remove pot from heat and fold in cheese.
Once melted, add macaroni and blend.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add bread crumbs and toss.
Distribute bread crumbs evenly over top of macaroni.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican salsa salad
directions: Combine macaroni, salsa, vinegar, cumin and chili powder. Stir in red beans, cheese and olives.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Toss before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving counts 1/2 fat, 1 1/2 pro., 1/2 vegetable and 1 bread.

title: strawberry eclair
directions: Mix vanilla pudding
by box directions. Add Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers and pudding mixture until used up. Mix strawberry gel with fresh berries and garnish the top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Layer bread, cooked meat and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and dry mustard together.
Pour over bread and meat and let set overnight.
Mix together soup and milk.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: southern salmon patties
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 1 cup liquid.
Melt margarine, add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and Tabasco.
Add milk mixture and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add drained salmon and 1/2 corn flakes to sauce.
Refrigerate or put in freezer for short time until firm enough to form into patties.
Roll in remaining flakes.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes on greased baking pan.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Cut pineapple into fine pieces.
Place in a bowl in layers, sprinkling each layer with sugar and marshmallows.
Cover and let stand several hours.
When ready to serve, fold in Cool Whip and spoon into serving dishes.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: *Mix together in a medium bowl.

title: fried fruit salad
directions: Put 1/4 cup margarine in hot skillet; put in apples.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add pineapple; continue cooking on high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add bananas, the juice of 1 lime and orange liqueur/Malibu rum, etc.; stir.
Add blueberries.
Stir.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add coconut any time.
Tastes great cold, too.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
Drain off fat drippings.
Saute vegetables 5 minutes or until soft.
Add the rest of the ingredients except the olives and cheese.
Bake in a greased 2-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with olives and cheese and bake 15 minutes more.
Allow 1/2 hour for reheating.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: Mix stuffing and press lightly in bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
In saucepan, stir milk into soup.
Add other ingredients.
Heat and turn into pie shell.
Top with buttered bread crumbs or croutons.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vegetable soup for canning
directions: Cook butter beans, peas and green beans until tender.
Add corn, okra, onions, peppers, salt and sugar.
Simmer slowly until tender.
Cook tomatoes in a separate pot and combine with vegetables. Put in quart jars and seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in a baking dish in oven.
In a mixing bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and mix well; add corn and mix.
Pour into the melted margarine in dish and bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: veggie weggies
directions: Mix together cream cheese and dressing.
Add milk until spreadable.
Lay flat, on a cookie sheet, the croissants and bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in the butter with a pastry blender.
Place sliced apples in an unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle crumb mixture over top.
Add cream.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until apples are soft and a rich syrup has formed.

title: banana split torte
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each in mixture of 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
Grease Bundt pan well. Place nuts in bottom of pan.
Add layers of biscuits.
Combine margarine, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and brown sugar.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan. Melt Hershey bar and syrup and set aside to cool.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend whipped cream and cream cheese together.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Freeze.
Serve semi-thawed and cut into squares.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Cover 2 cookie sheets with heavy brown paper. Brush with oil. In a large bowl, beat the egg whites until soft peaks.
Gradually beat in the sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, until egg whites are stiff. Gently fold in the walnuts and dates.
Drop in heaping teaspoonfuls on sheets.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour. Turn off. Leave overnight.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: divinity candy
directions: Into a saucepan, put 3 cups sugar, 2/3 cup water and syrup. In second saucepan, put 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Let contents of both pans come to a slow boil and boil until it makes a thread several inches long.
Have ready the beaten egg whites in a large mixing bowl and when stiff, pour in the contents of second pan and beat.
Then add the contents of the first pan.
Mix together and add nuts and vanilla.
Then beat together and when stiff drop from spoon onto a sheet of waxed paper.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all together and roll into small balls. Dip in sugar. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: mountain oysters
directions: Slice oysters like tomatoes.
Bread with flour, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: meatball hash brown bake
directions: In a bowl, lightly beat eggs. Stir in cracker crumbs, garlic, 1 tsp. salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Crumble beef over mixture; mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls. In a covered skillet over low heat, cook meatballs in a small amount of water until browned; drain.

In a bowl, combine the soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and remaining salt and pepper. With paper towels, pat hash browns dry. Stir into the soup mixture. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Arrange meatballs over top, pressing lightly into mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer or until meat is no longer pink and potatoes are tender.

title: chicken stir fry
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Spray skillet with Pam.
On medium heat, cook chicken until done.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix all together; bring to boil.
Boil one minute.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and nuts if you like.
Pour over all; stir good. Bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Combine sour cream, soup, pimentos and 1 3/4 cups cheese.
Stir in broccoli and onion mixture.
Place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole and top with 1/4 cup cheese and cracker crumbs or buttered stuffing mix. Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all the water is gone.
Mix applesauce, sweetener, eggs and oil.
Add all other ingredients; blend well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° until tested done with a toothpick.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Spray skillet very heavy with Pam.
Slice chicken breasts very thin.
Stir-fry in 1 tablespoon oil.
Remove.
Stir-fry the stir-fry vegetables in 1 tablespoon oil; add chicken.
In saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar, water, cornstarch and soy sauce. Stir well.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Serve with rice.

title: eskimo cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Put margarine in a bowl; let stand until soft.
Beat margarine with a fork or wooden spoon; stir in sugar, water, vanilla and cocoa.
Then mix in oats.
Shape into 36 balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: tomato salad mold
directions: In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over tomato juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until gelatine is dissolved.
Add dressing and stir.
Chill mixture until it begins to thicken. Fold in tomato, green pepper and cucumber.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart mold or 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm.

title: rhubarb coffee cake(no fat!)
directions: Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash pinto beans and garbanzo beans together in a small bowl.
Add onion and spices to beans.
Place 2 tablespoons of bean mixture in center of each tortilla and roll up.
Place rolled tortillas in a small glass baking dish and pour salsa over tortillas.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 minutes until slightly brown.
Garnish with thin slices of tomato.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Brown the meat and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: crunchies
directions: Heat brown sugar and Karo to a boil.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: no cook candy
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Roll the mixture into balls and they are ready to eat.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.
Add peppers to your liking.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix oleo into flour real well.
Pour ice water and mix in eggs and salt.
Roll out in good flour.
Cut in strips.
Add yellow food color into pot of boiling broth.
Drop strips into boiling broth. Cook about 30 minutes at reduced heat.

title: sausage supreme
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet and brown it.
Pour off excess fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer at the lowest possible heat for about 1 hour.

title: gazpacho salad(very cool and refreshing)
directions: Combine vegetables, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine with cold water.
Let set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Add vegetables. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: cucumbers with dill
directions: Peel cucumbers or score lengthwise with fork tines.
Cut into very thin slices.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and let stand two hours.
Wash off salt; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber slices.
Marinate at least one hour in refrigerator before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add chicken to other ingredients; put in casserole dish and cook until brown at 450°; usually takes 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in suet.
Add onions; cook until brown.
Add beans, garlic, water and tomatoes.
Season to taste.
Simmer until the flavors are well blended.

title: salted peanut rolls
directions: Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper.
In a medium bowl, combine 1/2 cup powdered sugar with marshmallow creme; blend and knead in remaining sugar.
Divide mixture into 4 parts.
Form each part into a rope 1/2-inch in diameter and cut into pieces 1 1/2-inches long.
Place these on wax paper and freeze about 20 minutes until firm.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In large bowl, arrange lettuce, pepper, onion and peas in layers.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over peas.
Sprinkle sugar, then cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with bacon just before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring potatoes, onion and water to a boil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice until potatoes are tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes for flavor to develop.
Add ham or tuna, if desired.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix all together.
Form into a ball and roll in parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan delight
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in butter until crumbly (it will be dry).
Press this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° (325° in glass pan).
While this is baking, beat milk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in nuts. Spread this over baked crust.
Bake approximately 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before serving.

title: mock mincemeat
directions: Mix chopped apples and tomatoes with other ingredients.
Stir to keep from burning.
Cook until clear.
Seal in glass jars.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Put sugar, flour and cornmeal in bowl.
Toss lightly with fork.
Add eggs, butter, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: In punch bowl, mix Kool-Aid, water and pineapple juice and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: beet-pineapple salad
directions: Drain beets and pineapple.
Use the juices and enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Some lemon juice can be used.
Bring the liquid to a boil and dissolve the gelatin.
Cut beets into small strips.
When gelatin is partially set, add pineapple, beets, celery and nuts.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Heat sugar, marshmallows and milk until bubbly (5 to 6 minutes). Remove from heat. Add butter and chocolate chip morsels. Cool slightly.
Makes enough for 2 layer cake.
Delicious.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Into a 2-quart casserole, sprinkle the rice.
Add soup and milk; mix slightly.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle soup mix over all.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 2 hours.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except marshmallows; put in casserole dish and bake at 400°.
Put marshmallows on top; heat through and serve.

title: milk shake
directions: How to make:
Put ingredients into a blender and mix.
Pour into tall glasses.
Top with additional ice cream before serving, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach until all water is off.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add spinach and form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 50.

title: raisin rice custard
directions: Bring milk to a boil; add raisins.
When cool, add beaten eggs, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly, then stir in rice with a fork.
Turn mixture into a greased baking dish. Set dish in a pan containing a little hot water and bake in moderate oven, 325° to 350°, until knife thrust in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Rather slow baking is trick of getting rice custard like texture to pudding.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa, then add beaten egg yolks with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix very good, then add 2 1/2 cups milk.
Now turn heat on medium.
Cook mixture until it thickens.
Add butter/oleo, vanilla and salt.
Beat 4 egg whites.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sweet corn relish
directions: Cook 1 hour.
Seal while hot.
All vegetables must be chopped.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger meat with onion.
Make sauce by mixing soup, cheese, evaporated milk and green chili.
Watch mixture as it will burn on the bottom.
Roll enchiladas by softening tortillas (either in oil or in the microwave) and adding hamburger and Longhorn cheese.
After all enchiladas are rolled, place in 9x13 pan.
Pour sauce over top and bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or so.
Also may use shredded chicken instead of meat. Make
6-8 servings.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Marinate spareribs in white wine overnight.
Mix well sugar, pepper, onion and garlic cloves.
Pour over spareribs and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in fat in skillet.
Make layers in casserole of rice (from box) and green beans.
Add sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Top with pork chops.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sweet-sour kraut
directions: Mix salad oil, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and cold water. Add to vegetables and chill for 12 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
You can substitute pumpkin pie spice for the cinnamon and nutmeg, if desired.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all fruit through grinder, skins included.
Stir in sugar. Set in refrigerator overnight in glass dish.
Serve with cold cuts.

title: scripture cake(bible cake)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift and measure flour with baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir in honey and spices.
Add raisins, figs and almonds.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost or serve plain.
Let set until cool.
Slice and eat.

title: christmas oyster stew
directions: Slowly heat oysters and butter in saucepan until edges of oysters start to curl.
At the same time, heat milk and half and half in another pan until small bubbles start to form around outside edge of milk.
(Do not boil.)
Combine milk, pepper and oysters and heat through.
(Do not boil.)
Salt to taste and serve with crackers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred the cabbage and chop the peppers, pimento and onions. Mix.
Put all the other ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a good rolling boil and pour over the vegetables while hot.
Mix again.
Make at least a day ahead.
Keeps well.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: chili hot dip
directions: In microwave, heat chili and Cheez Whiz.
Stir well.
Add cream cheese.
Heat and mix well.
Add 1/2 jar salsa, if desired. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix and cool.
Slice each layer in half.
Separate. Mix sugar with coconut (save part for icing).

title: petal bread
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; dissolve.
Add butter, egg, sugar and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Roll out and cut into 30 diamonds.
Dip each into melted butter; layer in Bundt pan.
Let rise again, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Place 8 slices of bread on cookie sheet with sides touching.
Mix together chicken, eggs, mushrooms, onion and mayonnaise.
Spoon this mixture over the bread, covering completely.

title: scalloped deluxe hash browns
directions: Put potatoes, soups, sour cream, onion and green peppers in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes or until ingredients can be mixed.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine with all other ingredients except nuts; mix well. Form into a ball.
Put on waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator and chill. Roll ball in chopped nuts and wrap in waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator until time to serve. Will serve 25.

title: quick microwave fudge
directions: In large glass mixing bowl, combine and blend sugar and cocoa. Add milk and margarine.
Do not stir.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir just enough to combine ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased 8-inch square glass dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix with eggs, sugar, potatoes and milk together with enough flour to make a sponge that will drop from spoon. Put to raise at 11:00. At 1:30 take 1 quart of flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup butter. Pour in sponge and make dough not quite as stiff as for bread.
About 4:00 make into rolls to let raise and serve at 6:00.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain rotini. Mix all ingredients together and chill. Makes 8 cups.

title: ratatouille
directions: In olive oil, starting with the garlic, saute until pale, then add onions and peppers.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover, then simmer 15 more minutes to reduce water.
Serve hot or cold with sour cream.

title: oyster corn chowder
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat 8 minutes.
Stir in celery, corn, onion flakes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, stir in oysters, milk, butter, and pepper over low heat.
Garnish with bacon.

title: x-tra fast cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place margarine in 9x13 baking dish. Heat in oven until melted.	Combine milk, flour and sugar in bowl. Pour into melted margarine.
(DO NOT STIR.)
Arrange fruit on top. (DO NOT STIR.)
Bake 40 minutes or until light brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 12.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Pinch all seams together.
Spread uncooked sausage over entire section of dough.
Sprinkle shredded cheese evenly over sausage.
Roll the entire section into one log.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring cocoa, sugar and milk to a boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add margarine. Stir until melted. Add peanut butter. Stir until melted. Add oats and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: speedy banana sauce
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients; cook over medium heat until thick. Add the vanilla; thin with mild vinegar, if necessary.
Slice bananas lengthwise; spread with peanut butter.
Pour cooled sauce over bananas for an after school treat, a dessert or on lettuce leaves.
Makes an interesting salad.

title: texas bread
directions: In a large bowl (not a metal bowl), mix yeast, sugar, shortening, egg, salt and warm water.

title: noodles with cabbage
directions: Grate cabbage, or if preferred, may be sliced as for cole slaw.
Sprinkle with salt and allow to stand 1 hour.
Squeeze water out.
Melt the margarine; add onion, sugar and caraway seed and cook until tender.
Add cabbage; keep turning and simmer until done.
This takes about 25 minutes.
Season with black pepper.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan only.
Mix brownie mix as directed on box.
Fold in white chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Do not let mixture boil.
Serves about 16 (1/2-ounce) cups.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa into a pot.
Bring to a boil for one minute.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon droplets onto wax paper.
Let harden and serve.
Serves 3 dozen.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Lightly fry onion in butter until brown.
Add meat, carrots, gravy and seasonings.
Mix together; pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pickled radish rounds
directions: Slice radishes very thin. A mandolin will do a good job. Put them in a bowl with the onions. In a jar with tight fitting lid, combine balance of ingredients and shake well. Pour over radish mixture. Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours.

title: alice foley's cinnamon-peanut cookies
directions: The cinnamon really
brings
out the full peanut butter flavor of these cookies.
They
are
so
fast
and easy, I use just a bowl and a handheld electric beater or mixer.

title: jiffy cinnamon rolls
directions: Have greased pans, brown sugar , butter and cinnamon ready.

title: caramel cake icing
directions: Boil 5 minutes; cook, beating in confectioners sugar a little at a time.
Beat well until thick enough to hold shape on cake. Add vanilla.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a 15 x 9-inch casserole dish with 4 to 6 slices of bacon. Sprinkle rice over bacon.
Place 6 to 8 chicken breasts over rice.
Sprinkle Lawry's blend garlic salt.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 soup can of milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: pasta and meat sauce
directions: 1. Add olive oil to skillet.
Add sausage and ground beef. Transfer to casserole.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix soup with mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Make a layer of broccoli, then chicken, then soup mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Crush crackers; saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add crumbs, scallops and 2/3 of the cheese.
Mix together thoroughly. Put into a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with remaining cheese. Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: In a large bowl or container, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store mix in a tightly covered container.

title: flourless chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter 9-inch springform pan (2 3/4-inch sides). I spray with Pam. Combine 8 ounces chopped chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; stir until melted and smooth. Cool lightly. Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar in large bowl until well blended. Stir in chocolate mixture. Beat egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff but not dry. Using rubber spatula, gently fold beaten whites into chocolate mixture in 3 additions. Pour into prepared pan. Bake about 30 minutes until puffed and tester (straw or toothpick) comes out with moist crumbs attached. Remove from pan and cool 10 minutes. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate overnight.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and cut up.
Beat eggs and fold in all ingredients.
Pour into flat pan (9 x 9-inches) and cover.
Let stand overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven eggs and bacon
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook bacon in skillet until almost crisp.
Add onion.
Cook, stirring frequently, until bacon is crisp; drain.
Spread bacon and onion in bottom of casserole dish.
Beat baking mix, eggs, milk, salt and pepper until almost smooth.
Slowly pour mixture over bacon; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 35 minutes).

title: jiffy hamburger buns
directions: Stir together 2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, oil, honey and salt until very warm (120° to 130°).
Pour into yeast and flour mixture.
Beat 3 minutes with electric mixer or by hand 300 strokes.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Beat well or knead briefly.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick on well-floured surface.
Cut into 3 or 4 inch rounds with canning jar ring or tuna can.
Let rise on greased baking sheets for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Makes 12 to 15 buns.
Recipe may be doubled.
Rounds cut 1/4-inch thick may be stacked before baking for an easily split hamburger bun.
For hot dog buns pull the round into an oblong shape.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheeses, milk, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Let cook until cheeses are melted.
Cook macaroni according to directions. Drain macaroni.
Mix macaroni together with other ingredients and empty into a well-sprayed casserole dish.
Bake for one hour.

title: meat muffins
directions: Roll out canned biscuits to make a rectangle, 12 x 9 x 1/2-inch, cut into squares.

title: amish vanilla pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Slowly stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Let cool.
Combine next 6 ingredients; mix well until crumbly.
Pour cooled mixture into pie shell; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and place half in the bottom of the tray or an 11 x 17-inch pan
(I use a flower pot).
Save the rest of the crushed cookies for top.
Using mixer, blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
In a bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat mixture until consistency of pudding.
Combine both mixtures and pour over layer of crushed Oreos.
Sprinkle the remaining Oreos on top.
Refrigerate until serving time.
For double or triple recipe, layer the Oreos and mixtures several times.
Place gummy worms on top.

title: layered chicken-black bean enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spray 2-quart glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. In medium bowl, combine chicken, cilantro, black beans and chiles; mix well. Spoon 2 tablespoons enchilada sauce in bottom of

baking dish. Place 4 tortillas over sauce. Spoon half chicken mixture over tortillas; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon 1/2 sauce and 1/2 sour cream randomly over cheese. Repeat layers; cover with foil. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and saute onion (3 minutes). Stir in flour; cook and stir for 1 minute.
Blend in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until boiling and mixture thickens.
Stir in celery, sugar, salt, pepper and corn.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
In small bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Stir 1 cup hot mixture into eggs.
Return to soup.
Heat but do not boil. Stir in chopped parsley.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: paul's pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Chop up pepperoni and slice black olives.
Add to pasta.
Toss with Kraft Zesty Italian and cheese.

title: breakfast delight(6 to 8 servings)
directions: In large bowl beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper, nutmeg and dry mustard.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, greased, lay 6 slices of bread. Sprinkle half of both cheeses evenly on top of bread, then all the meat.
Put the next 6 slices on top of meat, then rest of the cheese.
Sprinkle onion and green pepper on top.
After egg mixture is beaten together, pour evenly over first part. Refrigerate overnight or may be frozen for a later time.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If frozen, about 20 minutes longer.

title: aberdeenshire tipsy laird
directions: Split the sponge cakes and spread thickly with the jam and arrange along the bottom and sides of a tall glass bowl, trifle bowl or compote stand.
Sprinkle with finely grated lemon rind. Mix the brandy and sherry together and pour over the sponge cake, allowing it to soak in thoroughly.
Pour over the custard and refrigerate and allow to stand until cold and firm.
Whip the cream until floppy; add white sugar and vanilla flavoring to taste.
Pile this over the top of the custard and decorate the tip with cherries or chopped nuts.
A sprig of mint can be added in the center of bowl to garnish if desired.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter, gently.
Combine with soups, broth, chilies and chicken pieces (I add a dash of sherry).

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cut off broccoli flowerets.
Wash, rinse and set aside.
Peel onions and cut in 8 sections.
In a nonstick skillet, pour 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add garlic and broccoli.
Cook over medium heat until broccoli turns dark green (about 2 minutes).
Add onions and olive oil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring.
Add tomatoes and a few dashes of soy sauce.
Cover and heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: toad in the hole
directions: On washday, we had navy bean soup, cooked with our own country ham.
Mother did the laundry, and our responsibility was to have dinner ready when she came in and Daddy came in from the field to eat.
We often had mustard greens, alongside, that had been canned.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice. Beat until smooth.
Mix in cabbage and carrot.
Refrigerate at least a couple of hours before serving.

title: pastel cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
These cookies can also be made using a cookie press.

title: lemon herbed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic, Season-All, pepper and lemon herb seasoning.
Arrange chicken in a shallow casserole dish and pour the lemon and oil mixture over it.
Cover and bake until tender, about 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes longer to allow chicken to brown.
To serve, sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: date pudding cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soak dates in hot water; do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except the whipped topping.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine syrup, butter, sugar and cinnamon in sauce kettle.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place sweet potatoes in casserole dish.
Bake in hot oven, basting with syrup mixture frequently until potatoes are glazed and hot through. Serves 4.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients well, but do not overwork.
Roll out approximately 1 1/2 to 2 inches thick.
Cut; bake until golden brown.
Melt some margarine and spread over tops of biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature, and stir in a bowl. Shred ham and place in a bowl.
Cut up green onions and put in a bowl.
Mix altogether and shape into a ball.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes in a large bowl and mix well.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole. Top with cornflakes and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: wine punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve immediately.
Makes 5 1/2 quarts.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Melt butter and mix with dry ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 - 50 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings(hot)
directions: Marinate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn after 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coarsely chop onion and brown in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Remove onion from oil and set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to the pan and brown chicken which has been dredged with flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, garlic and coarsely chopped sweet green pepper.
Return browned onion to the pan and simmer chicken and vegetables, covered, for 15 minutes on low heat.
Add wine, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: greek spanikopitas
directions: Saute butter, onions, spinach and garlic in skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Transfer mixture to bowl and add cheeses.
Stir until blended.
Take 2 sheets of phyllo dough and cut in 1 1/2-inch strips.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture on each strip and fold into a triangle.
When mixture is consumed by all the dough, brush each spanikopita with butter.
Bake on baking sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 25 to 30 and makes an outstanding appetizer.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish. Cover with sliced Swiss cheese; mix soup and wine. Spread over cheese and chicken. Spread herb dressing over all. Drizzle with margarine. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green dragon dessert
directions: Blend cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl mix 2 packages of instant pistachio pudding with 2 cups of cold milk.
Beat as directed on package.
It will look like green wallpaper paste.
Completely fold in Cool Whip and softened vanilla ice cream.
Pour over crumbs and top with chocolate chips.
Freeze.

title: carrot ring
directions: Put all ingredients into blender for about 30 seconds until smooth.
Pour into greased ring or casserole and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Unmold (if baked in a ring) onto a warm plate.

title: orange fluff
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add box of jello to drained fruit.
Mix well.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal macaroons(yields 20 cookies)
directions: Combine the cinnamon and the melted shortening; then beat the egg and gradually add the sugar.
Next stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until delicately browned.
Remove from the baking sheet while still warm.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Prepare lime jello according to package directions.
Pour into a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan or 4 1/2-quart container.
Chill until almost set.
Dissolve lemon jello in hot water in top of double boiler.
Add marshmallows.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat with rotary beater until blended. Stir in 1 cup drained pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Chill until almost set.
Prepare cherry jello.
Chill until consistency of egg white.
Pour over pineapple layer.
Chill until firm.

title: grandpa fredrick's christmas pie
directions: Thaw Cool Whip and cream cheese at room temperature.
Melt Baker's chocolate in double boiler and mix 1/3 cup of milk.
Mix cream cheese and melted chocolate and sugar mix well, then stir in Cool Whip and walnuts.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Cover with lid and put in freezer until ready to eat.
Eat frozen or thawed.

title: cheese roll
directions: Place cheese and cream cheese in a large bowl.
Let come to room temperature.
Mix cheeses well.
Add nuts, garlic and salt. Mix well.
Make into 2 rolls and roll in chili powder.
Wrap in foil.
Chill until firm.

title: cream wafers(about 5 dozen)
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.

title: franks with sweet-sour cabbage
directions: In skillet, cook and stir cabbage in butter until lightly browned. Mix rest of ingredients except franks. Stir in cabbage. Place franks on top.

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and red pepper sauce.
Pour over avocados.
Toss. Stir in bacon, tomatoes and onion.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from freezer about 20 minutes before serving.

title: "lusciously" lemon layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.
Grate zest and squeeze juice from 2 lemons in bowl. Combine flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine 1 cup milk and 2 teaspoons of vanilla.
In another bowl, beat shortening and granulated sugar until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with milk mixture until just smooth. Stir in lemon zest and lemon juice.
Pour into pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove cakes from pans and cool completely on rack.

title: cream soup potato
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Stir in 2 cups diced potatoes, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 teaspoon dry mustard.
Heat thoroughly.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a golden brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring to a boil the Karo syrup and sugars.
Remove from heat, add
the
peanut
butter
and mix.
Then add the Spanish peanuts and
mix.
Next add the corn flakes and mix.
Pat into a 9
x 13-inch buttered pan.
Add the broken chocolate pieces. Warm in the
oven
until
able to spread the chocolate with a knife.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: colorful vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss the broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, onion and olives.
In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine dressing mix, oil and vinegar; shake well.
Pour over salad and toss.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Serves 20.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onions in margarine until translucent; add meat, garlic, salt, flour and Accent.
Simmer 20 minutes; add mushrooms, chicken and mushroom soup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix. Keep warm and serve over rice.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together with juice from pineapple and cherries.

title: strawberries with strawberries
directions: When cleaning berries, leave 2 cups damaged or bruised berries for sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken and debone, then mix in pot with onion, cream of celery soup, salt and pepper and milk. Let come to boil, then set aside.

Get casserole pan ready to line with the dressing, half on the bottom, put melted 1/2 stick margarine over the dressing then put all the mixture in pot over the dressing then top with rest of dressing and margarine.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: shipwreck
directions: Grease casserole.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Slice potatoes on bottom of casserole.
Cover potatoes with hamburger, salt and pepper.
Slice onion over hamburger.
Spread kidney beans over hamburger.
Pour undiluted soup over all ingredients.
Cover. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Serves 4.
A meal in one.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan melt 2 ounces chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread or brush over the bottom and up the sides of a pastry shell.
Chill.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread over chocolate layer; cover and chill for 2 hours.
Arrange strawberries, tip end up, atop filling.
Brush jam over berries. Melt remaining chocolate and drizzle over all.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, buttermilk and eggs.
In a pan bring to boil 2 sticks of margarine, cocoa and water.
Add the ingredients, a little at a time, and mix well.
If you like, add 1 cup chopped pecans (I normally do).
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: honor's casserole chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds and cornflakes.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with almonds and cornflakes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
(Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: snappy hamwich
directions: Spread bread with equal mayonnaise and mustard.

Layer each bread slice with 1 slice of ham, 4 slices apple and 1 slice cheese. Microwave on High 20 seconds or until cheese melts or place on cookie sheet and broil until cheese melts, and is lightly brown. Serve hot.
Makes 6.

title: lime-cream cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Let thicken slightly.
Beat softened cream cheese, mayonnaise or salad dressing and horseradish, adding small portions of the thickened gelatin.
Then fold in the remaining gelatin and mix well.
Add crushed pineapple, celery and nuts. Pour into large mold and chill until completely set.
Serves 12.

title: onion soup parmesan
directions: For croutons, cut French bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place cubes on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cubes are dry and crisp.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Cube cheese.
Break crackers slightly. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage, crumble and drain.
Prepare pie crust.
Mix cheese and sausage; sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and the egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zingy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and shape into loaf.
Place in a rack in a baking pan; bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings, containing 220 calories each.

title: small franks dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except franks in saucepan. Simmer for 20 minutes. Add franks or hot dogs, cut 1-inch long.
Mix in well. Pour in warming pot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let spiced vinegar come to a boil; add cucumbers and onions and bring to boiling point.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing bowl cream cheese, sugar, minced onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, unbeaten egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough. Beat well after each addition; cover.
Let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until light and doubled in size.
Usually it takes 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down dough.
Turn onto well greased 8-inch round 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Let rise in warm place until light, 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Pour over crushed pretzels. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add milk and mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Dump into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle crushed peanuts on top and freeze for 1 hour.

title: mustard ham sauce
directions: Combine sugar, flour, mustard, vinegar and butter.
Cook this mixture until boiling, stirring often.
Add water and catsup. Beat eggs slightly.
Add gradually to hot mixture.
Sauce may be served hot with ham or cold on sandwiches.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a good boil.
Add butter and milk; cook slowly to form soft ball stage.
Add popped corn.
Stir together.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and fill up rest with cold water to make 2 cups.
Break candy up in little pieces.
Then add jello to 2 cups hot water.
Mix together until candy melts.
Add rest of cold water, put in refrigerator and let almost jell.
Then add dream Whip and put back in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift cornstarch, 1 1/2 cups sugar and salt in top of double boiler; stir in boiling water and mix well.
Place over lower part of double boiler and stir until custard leaves side of pan.
Add egg yolks and cook 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and stir in butter. After butter has melted, add chocolate and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue of egg whites, beaten with remaining sugar.
Bake at 250° to 300° until golden brown.
Cool and serve.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Make biscuits with hands or roll out and cut.
Cook in moderate oven (about 425°) until brown.

title: gorp
directions: Use 1 cup of each ingredient.
Mix all together and store in plastic bags.
This is a high energy, high carbohydrate snack good for a quick energy boost.
I make this each summer for the hikers that participate in the Young Adult Wilderness Adventure sponsored by the D. O. C.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and add pork chops.
Brown both sides. Remove chops and drain off all but 4 tablespoons of fat.
Stir in the raw rice; be sure all grains are coated.
Place pork chops on top of rice, then place 1 slice of onion, a slice of lemon and 1 tablespoon of chili sauce on each chop.
Add tomato juice and Tabasco.
Cover tightly and bake 1 hour or until tender in a 325° oven.

title: best clam chowder
directions: Brown
onions
in butter.
Add clam liquor and potatoes. Cover and
cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat but do not boil.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: Put everything in clean half gallon jars, then finish filling the jars with cold water. Put on lids. Leave jars so that you can shake them to dissolve the salt.

title: easy ham and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a baking dish with butter.
Layer the ingredients; add cheese and enough milk to fill pan to about 2-inches from top.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour and cocoa in a heavy saucepan. Combine milk, egg yolks and melted butter and beat using a wire whisk, until mixture is well blended.
Gradually add milk mixture to sugar mixture, stirring until smooth.
Cook mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly (about 10 minutes).
Spoon into pastry shell; set aside.

Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed with an electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves (2 to 4 minutes).
Spread meringue over chocolate filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of large casserole dish with beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or at least 6 hours.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours, covered and 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chocolate marshmallow cups
directions: Place 4 marshmallows in 48 lined 1 3/4-inch muffin cups. Combine chocolate pieces, peanut butter and butter in 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Cook on low heat until melted.
Cool slightly. Spoon chocolate over marshmallows.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve cold!

title: chocolate soaked cherries
directions: If desired, soak cherries in brandy or Kahlua.
Drain 1/2 juice.
Add booze and put into refrigerator for 1 week.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and 2 teaspoon vanilla and beat well.
Sift flour and baking soda.
Add Quaker oats to flour mixture.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Blend and set aside.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-gallon freezer. Fill to the container line with milk.
Freeze.

title: pauline caster's cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Blend egg yolks and cottage cheese.
Blend in milk and flour. Lastly, fold in egg whites.
Let batter stand a few minutes.

title: dump it cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer applesauce, pineapple and nuts. Spoon over dry yellow cake mix.
Melt butter and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Combine milk, sugar and coconut extract.
Heat in saucepan to a boil.
Pour over baked cake while cake is still warm.
After cake is cooled, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine the packaged vegetables with celery and onion.
Boil 15 minutes and drain.
Add mayonnaise and dot the dish with the oleo.
Coat the crumbs with melted oleo and cover casserole. Cover with Reynolds Wrap and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and brown.
Serves 10 people.

title: grandma d's chicken casserole
directions: Mix in bottom of casserole dish the rice, water, soups and curry powder.
Place chicken parts (breasts or thighs) on top of this mixture.
Pour the dry onion soup over top of chicken.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: nutty broccoli salad
directions: Add gently to salad.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and eggs.
Cook about 6 minutes or until thick in the microwave.
After this has cooked, add the butter and vanilla.
After all this, mix and pour in pie crust. You should bake pie crust before pouring in the filling.
You may top with your favorite meringue topping.

title: green bean salad
directions: Beat together the last 6 ingredients.
Pour dressing over vegetables and let stand 24 hours.
Drain and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spinach with burghul
directions: Lightly brown onion in oil.
Add spinach, salt and pepper. Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle washed burghul on top of spinach.
Cover tightly and simmer for about 10 minutes or until burghul is tender.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer in large container and cover.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: quick dinner biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Split each biscuit 2-3 times, dip in butter and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Juice lemons
and
oranges
and
put
all
fruit juices together.
Allow to
stand	for 3 hours.
Boil spices in separate small amounts of water for 10 minutes.
Steep tea and add water. Mix and heat all ingredients.
Taste before adding all spices to water
to
prevent	too much spice.
Extra lemon and pineapple juice and slices of apples may be added for flavor.

title: frosty yule log
directions: Mix together.
Shape into a log.
Roll in nuts.
Garnish with olives.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 16 servings.
Each equals 1/2 P, 1/2 FA and 30 optional calories.
If using fat-free cream cheese, add 10 optional calories.

title: pumpkin slices
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add additional items in order given.
Pour into a greased 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: country barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, salt and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Put ham and potatoes into shallow, 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Melt 3 tablespoons oleo.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring until thickened. Pour over ham and potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Dot with rest of oleo.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.

title: fresh apple coffee cake
directions: Combine apple, 1/4 cup orange juice and cinnamon in bowl; stir and set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup orange juice and milk; stir and set aside.
Cream oleo; add sugar.
Beat on medium speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix.
Add 1/2 flour mixture to creamed mixture; add milk mixture.
Add remaining flour mixture.
Spray 10-inch tube pan with Mazola.
Pour in 1/2 of batter; top with 1/2 of apple mixture.
Pour remaining batter into pan; top with rest of apple mixture.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serves 16 (202 calories each).

title: chocolate chip pizza
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine melted oleo and brown sugar; mix.
Add egg, hot water and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread dough on pizza pan. Sprinkle with nuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Press mixture firmly to bottom and sides of dish. Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: bottom round roast
directions: Place roast in deep baking pan.
Place potatoes around the sides and carrots all around top of potatoes.
Sprinkle onion and garlic over carrots.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, covered.
Uncover; add water.
Bake at 200° for one more hour.
Cool down for 20 minutes. Slice thin.
Serve with juice or make gravy.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger in frying pan and pour off fat.
In a very large bowl, mix ingredients together.
Eat right away.
Feeds 4.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Put sugar, margarine or butter and milk in large buttered pan; cover with plastic wrap and poke holes.
Microwave on roast for 10 minutes.
Stir and roast 5 to 6 minutes more until soft ball forms in cold water, 236°.
Stir until melted the chocolate pieces.
Fold in marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Delicious and so fattening.

title: tropical banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Break bananas into 1-inch chunks.
Place in food processor.
Whirl until finely chopped. Scrape into liquid measure to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Combine eggs, rum, oil, sugar and bran cereal in processor.
Whirl 1 minute. Add baking powder, baking soda, salt, flour and coconut to processor.
Process with short on/off pulses just until combined. Scrape into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until golden and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: marilyn's meat dish
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in skillet and cook for 1 hour. Cook noodles.
Drain.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese and onions with hot noodles.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Layer meat sauce, noodles and meat sauce.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
May freeze or refrigerate overnight. Reheat until bubbly.

title: cocktail wieners and meatballs
directions: Heat catsup and jelly on low until jelly melts.
Make hamburger into very small balls and brown.
Pour sauce, meatballs and wieners in crock-pot and cook on high for at least 2 hours.
May be reheated several times.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mash sausage to break apart.
Add Bisquick slowly, adding a little water at a time to aid in mixing thoroughly.
Add cheese to sausage mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Can be made ahead of time and quick frozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese together.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Serve with strawberries, pineapple and any other fruit you like.

title: lemon fluff squares
directions: Put pineapple into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and spread evenly.
Put cake mix (dry) over pineapple and even out without mixing.
Do not stir!
Mix all other ingredients with beater and pour over cake evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
After cooling, cut into squares, size desired.

title: chinese beef and pea pods
directions: Marinate meat in mixture of salt, sugar, soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in frypan and stir-fry pea pods in hot pan for 2 minutes.
Remove pea pods.
Add another tablespoon oil to pan and heat garlic for 2 minutes, then add pea pods and blend together.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cream together the cheese and butter.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Roll thin between wax paper and cut with pastry cutter.
Bake in 325° oven.

title: chicken buns
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put tablespoon of mixture in center of crescent rolls or triangles of pie crusts.
Fold over and close.
Brush with melted butter.
Roll in crushed, seasoned croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nut goodie candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter. Spread half of mixture in 9 x 13 pan. Put in freezer to freeze. Cook margarine, milk and dry vanilla pudding. Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and maple flavoring.
Spread over frozen mixture.
Sprinkle cocktail peanuts. Spread the remaining mixture over the peanuts and freeze. Cut before freezing too hard, then freeze hard. Put in Tupperware with wax paper between layers. Keep frozen.

title: boiled pear dessert
directions: Preheat broiler.
Pat pears dry on paper towel.
Cut pears into 1/2-inch slices.
Put in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Broil 4 inches from heat source for 5 minutes.
Combine cream and vanilla.
Pour over pears. Broil 5 minutes or until sauce is golden and bubbly.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine pudding, Cool Whip and pineapple in a bowl; mix well. Stir in marshmallows, apples and pecans.
Chill before serving, at least 1 hour.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chips in saucepan.
Add condensed milk and vanilla.
Add walnuts.
Put in pan and chill.
Cut in squares.

title: banana whip
directions: Press bananas through sieve and put into a saucepan.
Add sugar and lemon juice; mixing well.
Bring just to a simmering point; stirring to mix well.

title: dill cucumbers
directions: Combine sour cream, dill, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cucumbers.
Chill for 1/2 hour; then serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits.
Dip each into margarine, then into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Stack unevenly in ring pan.
Bake at 435° for 20 to 25 minutes, turn onto plate. Drizzle powdered sugar icing over top, if desired.

title: low sugar lime jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries.
Any flavor of Jell-O may be used.
Chill thoroughly.

title: fudge pie (no crust)
directions: Melt cocoa and butter in saucepan, stirring over low heat. Cool slightly and add flour that has been mixed in with the sugar. Add the rest of the ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pie pan (no crust) and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Add enough water or broth to flour to form batter.
Pour batter into buttered skillet, forming large pancake.
Turn when batter is no longer white but looks slightly clearish.
Cook on second side just 30 seconds.
Remove pancake, cut into squares and add to chicken and chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder. Mix, roll and bake.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and water until jello dissolves.
Add rest of ingredients and chill until congealed.

title: chicken-veggie stir-fry
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of the dressing in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic powder.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until chicken is cooked through.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in remaining salad dressing and soy sauce.
Simmer for 1 minute.
Serve over hot, cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread according to package.
Bake well done.
Let cool.
Crumble and add taco seasonings.
Add other ingredients and fold well.
Refrigerate.
This salad will last about 4 days.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Cook noodles
according to package directions.	Crumble ground beef into
microwave
safe	colander,
place
over deep microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High setting for 5 to 6 minutes. Discard drippings.	Combine
beef,	spaghetti
sauce and mushrooms.	Place layer of cooked noodles, 1/3 meat sauce mixture, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/2 of Mozzarella in large Corning Ware casserole or Pyrex dish.
Continue layering, ending with layer of noodles,
topped with last of meat sauce mixture.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella
and
Parmesan	cheese on top.	Cover with glass top
or
plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast setting 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil and sugar; mix well.
Add squash, vanilla, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well; pour into greased pans.
Makes 2 loaves. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: anginetti cream puffs
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix whipped topping and cream cheese in bowl at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple and mix at low speed for 1 minute.
Cut cookies in half. Drop 1 teaspoon of filling on 1/2 of cookie. Replace top.
Refrigerate unused portions.

title: old fashioned date and nut roll candy
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water to soft ball stage; add nuts and beat until very stiff.
Pour onto wet cotton tea towel and form into a roll the size of 50 cent piece, then wrap in waxed paper. Slice as you serve.

title: flan
directions: Heat sugar in a heavy skillet, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and turns golden brown.
Quickly remove from heat and pour into a round cake pan (tip pan to distribute evenly).
Let cool.

Preheat oven to 350° and make custard by mixing eggs, evaporated milk, 1 cup sugar, vanilla and salt. Pour over caramel in pan and bake, standing in pan of hot water for 60 minutes, or until knife inserted in custard comes out clean.
Turn out onto flat dessert plate with rim when cooled.

title: jam cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add jam. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into three waxed paper-lined 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all dry ingredients together and put in shortening.
Add to milk and yeast; stir until well blended.
Grease light sided bowl and place all or part in a bowl.
Sit in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: black forest freezer pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into pie crust. Cover and freeze for about 15 minutes.

title: candy canes
directions: Mix together cream of tartar, corn syrup, water and sugar. Stir over heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 265° (very hard ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add peppermint.
Divide mixture in half.
Add food coloring to one part.
Pour on greased platters.
Pull each part separately into ropes.
Twist red part around white part.
Cut into 8-inch lengths.
Form into candy canes.

title: sweet 'n sour salad
directions: In large bowl mix broccoli, cauliflower, pimento, cheese, onion and bacon.
Mix and pour over veggies the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Stir well.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Just cover vegetables with water.
Add spices, but no salt. Put lid on pot and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli casserole #9
directions: Cook
broccoli	according
to package directions; drain well. Mix
all
other
ingredients and add to broccoli.
Pour into casserole and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Recipe can easily be doubled.)

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Melt cheese; add Ro-Tel and hamburger.
(Above is what the recipe says.)
I cube the cheese and put in glass dish and add the Ro-Tel sauce.
Then I put into microwave for 4 minutes, stir it and put back in the microwave for 4 more minutes.
Then I take it out and add the hamburger.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix everything together. Put in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool; cut into bars and enjoy.

title: albondigas(meatballs in soup)
directions: In a bowl, mix meat, rice, onion, garlic, tomato, egg, chopped fresh oregano, dash of dried oregano, salt and pepper.
Have water boiling in a medium stock pot.

title: betcha can't eat just one appetizer
directions: Brown ground beef
and	sausage.
Drain.
Add
oregano, pepper sauce and garlic.
Mix
in	skillet.
Add cubed cheese. Stir over low heat
until
melted.
Spread mixture on cocktail rye bread. Put on cookie sheets and freeze until firm.
Store in plastic bag in	freezer
until needed.	Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken l'orange(lo-cal)
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine diet soda and soy sauce and pour over chicken.
