Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning at 15 minute intervals.
If you have more chicken, just increase soy sauce and soda mixture, keeping the 2:1 ratio.

title: rice dessert
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Add marshmallows and mix.
Cool.
Add fruit cocktail and whipped cream and fold in. Refrigerate.

title: butterscotch chip bars
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients until fluffy.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Then cover with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven until soft.
Cool.

title: breakfast hash
directions: Brown potatoes in margarine.
Season with salt and pepper. Stir in sausage and green pepper.
Beat eggs and pour over potato mixture.
Cook until eggs thicken.
Great for large groups!

title: quick fruit cream
directions: Mix box of jello and cottage cheese; add pineapple, mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
That's it!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients;
bring to a boil. Add peanuts. Cook over high
heat,
stirring constantly, until light golden brown. Remove from heat;
stir in soda and pour into pans.
I use 3 pie tins, sprayed with Pam.

title: peach torte
directions: To egg yolks, add enough water to make 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons.
Combine with cake mix and beat 4 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.

title: tico tacos
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, cheese, tomato and seasonings.
Mix well.

title: hot rolls
directions: Bring water and milk to a boiling point, then let cool.
Mix yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add sugar, salt and potatoes to the cooled water and milk mixture.
Add yeast to mixture.
Knead well. Put into large bowl, let rise until doubled in size then make into rolls.
Let rise again until doubled in size, then bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into greased muffin tin. Bake at 425° approximately 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 18.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in sauce, onion and green pepper.
Blend cottage cheese and cream cheese. Spoon 1/2 noodles in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with some sauce and all of cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles and end with sauce.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Allow extra 15 to 20 minutes if cold from refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place corn in bowl and fill empty can with milk.
Add sugar, salt and eggs and mix together.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel-pecan cookies
directions: Combine four and baking soda;
set aside.
Beat together butter, sugar and brown sugar;
mix in egg, half & half and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture, then stir in pecans and Rolo candies, cut in half.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto baking sheets and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: betty's buttery bite-sized tarts
directions: Tarts: For pastry, in a mixing bowl, beat softened margarine or butter and cream cheese until thoroughly combined. Stir in the flour.

title: cola roast
directions: Place roast in baking dish. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Pour in Coke. Cover and seal tightly with foil. Bake at 300° until tender.

title: spaghetti hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Add spaghetti and pork and beans.
Stir all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: my favorite banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip crushed bananas until very light. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix, then flour and soda and mix very well.
Add nuts and mix, then bananas.
Turn this mixture into a very well-greased bread pan (glass works better) and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: favorite meatballs
directions: Mix egg, saltines and beef together and form into balls. Roll balls in flour and brown in a skillet; set aside to drain. Mix soup, milk and catsup. Place meatballs in baking dish. Pour on soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until soup mixture begins to thicken.

title: saw dust salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water. Add pineapple. Add layer of bananas and a layer of marshmallows. Then chill.

title: butter brickle cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and almond flavoring to creamed mixture; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt; add to mixture.
Add crushed candy bars to dough mixture.
Shape in rolls and wrap each in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices and bake at 350° about 7 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: fay's sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls (walnut size). Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apricot pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter loaf pan.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, then apricot puree and pecans.
Sift together remaining ingredients and mix into batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake until tester inserted in center comes out clean (45 minutes). Cool 10 minutes in pan, then invert and cool completely.
When fresh apricots are out of season, I use a combination of canned and dried to make 1 cup.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and start layering the ingredients, beginning with a layer of crumbs and alternate with squash mixture.
End with crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or 35 minutes if prepared ahead and refrigerated. This recipe is best if you use fresh yellow squash from your garden!
In Arizona - Ha!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Flavor is better if refrigerated 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and set aside.
Mix together coconut and pecans.
Set aside.
Cream together oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Sprinkle the pecan and coconut mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cake mix on pecan and coconut mixture.
With a spoon, drop dollops of cream cheese mixture evenly over top of cake mix.
Do not stir into cake.
Make the dollops hit as missiles over cake top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Do not overbake.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Cook cranberries in 2 cups water until soft. Strain juice. Add all other ingredients. Then add extra water to thin it nicely. Heat and serve.

title: sizzling hot and sour soup(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Soak mushrooms in warm water for 30 minutes, thereafter drain, cut off stems and thinly slice caps.
Bring broth to boil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; stir for 3 minutes.
Stir in all ingredients except cornstarch and egg.
Return to boil, then add the cornstarch.
Stir until thickens.
Remove pot from heat. Slowly drizzle in egg, stirring constantly.

title: chili
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in skillet until well done.

title: flounder with dill
directions: Place tomato slices in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Arrange fillets on top of tomatoes.
Combine bread crumbs and next 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in margarine. Sprinkle evenly over fillets.
Bake at 425° for 13 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Garnish with fresh dill, if desired.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in tube pan.

title: minted hot cocoa mix
directions: Place candy in a heavy duty zip-top bag.
Crush candy with a mallet.
Combine crushed candy and remaining ingredients.
Store in an air tight container.

title: sour cream mince pie
directions: In saucepan, combine chopped apples, juice and crumbled mincemeat; bring to boil.
Cook 2 minutes after boiling.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
In small bowl, beat sour cream, eggs, flour, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of baked mincemeat.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until topping is set.
Cool; chill before serving.

title: lemon-pineapple dessert
directions: Cook until thick; cool.
Pour into dish with granola (preferably blueberry or nut granola) and cool in fridge.
Top with fine coconut, if desired.

title: best corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and stir in corn meal.
Blend in oleo, egg and milk.
Combine well.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry and combine just to moisten.
Pour in greased 7 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes (or until done).

title: coated nuts
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Stir almost constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and walnut meats. Pour on wax paper and separate with a fork.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix into pineapple.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all and refrigerate.

title: quick vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat removed from bone in hot oil or bacon grease.
Add beans, water, tomatoes, onion and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables; simmer until vegetables are soft.
Remove bones and bay leaves before serving.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook until tender the broccoli and cauliflower.
Heat and pour over vegetables the cream of chicken or celery soup and Cheez Whiz.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle top with 1 can French's fried onion rings.
Return to oven and brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: mexicali pork chops
directions: A few dashes of hot pepper sauce can be added, if you like it a little spicer.

title: cream of parisian soup
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in 2 cups water until just tender. Melt oleo and saute celery and onion until slightly clear.
Add 1 cup flour.
Stir until blended.
Crush the 4 bouillon cubes and add to the flour, celery and onion mixture.
Add 6 cups cold milk slowly and stir until thick and smooth.
Add cooked vegetables plus the liquid.
Season to taste.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: lemon buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light like whipped butter. Add eggs, one at a time, and continue beating.
Slowly add flour, buttermilk, salt, hot water, flavoring and soda, beating all the while.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing.

title: caramel ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Place orange marmalade in various spots and sprinkle with nuts.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and set aside.
Separate biscuits.
Dip biscuits in melted butter and then sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in pan, space evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture and drizzle remaining butter over top.
Bake near center of oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool upright in pan. Invert onto plate and serve.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler and mix with mayonnaise.
Then fold in the hash browns.
Cover with crumbled bacon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into a ball, then roll in chopped pecans or parsley.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: cherry (fruit) pudding
directions: If you use cherry filling, omit cinnamon and add 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract.
Other flavors use original ingredients.

title: quick rolls in muffin pan
directions: Stir all ingredients together and spoon into a Pam-sprayed muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake approximately 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash drained artichokes with fork, or use food processor with plastic blade.
Add cheese and mayonnaise and mix well.
Add lemon juice, tabasco and garlic powder.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Put into shallow casserole and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with bread sticks, chips or crackers.
Serves 12.

title: tzatziki sauce
directions: Mix the garlic and cucumber into the yogurt.
Season lightly and chill.
Serve sprinkled with the mint.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare and cool bacon.
Crumble bacon and toss with the broccoli and onion. Pour dressing on and mix well.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and saute onions.
Add seasonings and mushroom liquid.
Blend in chicken soup and stir until smooth and thickened.
Cook spaghetti (broken in 2-inch pieces) in 1 1/2 quarts salted, boiling water.
Drain and rinse with hot water. Mix with chicken mixture.
Add chicken and put in buttered casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes or until center of casserole is hot.
Bake at 325°.

title: venison jerky
directions: Soak venison overnight in salt, water and vinegar.
Next morning, wash and then parboil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Get bacon or fatback; cut up small and fry crisp.
Season venison good with salt, lots of pepper, garlic and meat tenderizer.
Then fry in bacon fat to brown.
Put in 2 cups of water, cut up 1 or 2 onions and 1 bell pepper and add to meat.
Cook until tender, then add celery and carrots.
Make sauce with barbecue sauce and pour gravy in pot off.
Add barbecue sauce and put in oven or simmer in pot until done.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Scrub squash, cut of ends and slice to make 6 cups.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix sour cream, egg yolks and flour.
Fold in egg whites. In a 10 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half the squash, half the egg mixture and half the cheese; sprinkle bacon on top. Repeat layers of squash, egg and cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle atop.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with bacon and parsley.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream the margarine and blend in the corn syrup, brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in the oats.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Melt the chips and peanut butter together on low heat. Spread over top of baked crust.
Refrigerate until cool. Cut into squares.

title: layered salad
directions: Chill, then mix before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Cook until thick. Add coconut.
Stir well and put in a baked pie shell.

title: string beans
directions: Wash the beans twice in cold water.
Put in 4-quart pot with the other ingredients.
Cover with water and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauteed scallops with garlic
directions: Wash and dry scallops and shake them in flour.
Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Add scallops; cook them very quickly, tossing them in the oil so that all sides are browned.
While they are cooking, add the finely chopped garlic and mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Just before removing from heat, add parsley and toss to coat.
Scallops cook quickly, depending on size and will be done in 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: gumdrop popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter; stir well.
Pour over popcorn, peanuts and gumdrops.
Grease hands with dab of butter and form the popcorn mixture into balls.

title: super stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in a little oil.
Add cut up onions and paprika. Simmer for at least 2 hours.
Onions and beef will render liquid, but water can be added if necessary.
Just before serving, add sour cream to lighten sauce.
Serve over wide noodles.

title: zia angelina's biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar and butter until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and orange juice.
Lastly, add chocolate morsels.
Turn out on floured board and separate into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into a 10 to 12-inch log.
Place 2 logs on a baking sheet, greased.
Bake approximately 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Slice into 1-inch slices when cooled.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix soup with sugar, oil and vinegar. Pour over vegetables; cover and chill overnight. This will keep for several days.

title: la madeleine pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl. In another bowl, mix pumpkin and corn syrup until well blended. Mix into dry ingredients.
Add cream and eggs; mix until well combined.
Pour the mixture into an unbaked 10-inch pie shell. Bake 45 minutes.
Cool and decorate with fresh whipped cream, if desired.

title: fresh berry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Prepare and wash fresh berries. Add sugar and set aside. Blend together in saucepan flour and water (or juice). Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly. Add berry mixture and cook over low heat until just tender. Pour hot mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Dot with butter or margarine and add spices if desired. Prepare Sweet Drop Biscuit Dough Recipe (found in Bread section). Drop batter from a spoon onto berry mixture. Do not stir. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve hot, with cream if desired. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Cook blackberries until done.
Strain juice and sweeten to taste.
Heat juice to boiling.
Roll out 1 can biscuits.
Cut into thin squares.
Drop into boiling juice.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: favorite meat loaf topping
directions: Stir all together.
When meat loaf is nearly done (for the last 15 minutes), put this sauce on top.
Serve.

title: randy's pineapple delight cake
directions: In sheet cake pan, dump can of pineapple, juice and all, and spread evenly.
Add apricots and juice.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly on top of fruit mixture.
Pour melted butter over the top of cake mix evenly.
Add nuts to top.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Keep refrigerated after it cools.

title: savory crescent chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls and make 4 squares.
Put 1/4 mixture in center of each square.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center.
Seal edges. Brush top with melted oleo.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
I cut up onion and celery in a bowl with a tablespoon of oleo on top in the microwave before adding to chicken mixture.
Make gravy to put over top of them.

title: apple pie
directions: Grate or slice apples to cover dish with good layer.
Cover apples with loaf bread, trimmed and cut in strips.
Pour mixture of sugar, flour and margarine over bread.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Also is good using peaches.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Combine next 6 ingredients and add. Add eggs and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: unbelievable biscuits(low fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees.
Combine all ingredients, except spray.
Mix until well blended. I use my food processor for this. The mixture will be really sticky and moist.
Spoon onto a well-floured surface. Roll the dough around in the flour until lightly coated.
This makes it easier to work with the soft dough. Knead lightly with the fingertips about 6 times.
Press or roll the dough to a thickness of about 1/2 inch. Cut with a 2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a baking sheet that has been lightly coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 475 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
When you take the biscuits out of the oven, spray the tops with "I Can't Believe It's Not Butter" spray. This gives the biscuits a soft top.
Makes about 6 to 7 biscuits with less than 1 gram of fat per biscuit.

title: hawaiian fruit compote
directions: Combine pineapple chunks, tangerine, banana, strawberries, orange juice concentrate and soda in a large bowl.
Toss gently. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: curried cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator.
Pile on English muffins and heat under broiler until melted.
Use Melba rounds for hors d'oeuvres.

title: peppy polynesian chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces, skin side up, in a 400° oven or under the broiler to melt fat from the skin.
Arrange the browned chicken, skin side up, in a baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until tender, about 25 minutes, basting occasionally with the sauce.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant antipasto
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer about 30 minutes.
Use as dip or over rice.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour half of prepared cake batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Pour melted caramel
mixture over baked cake.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and the chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over this and sprinkle with the remaining nuts.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: cristy's festive baked beans
directions: In baking dish mix beans and fixin's and all ingredients listed.
Top with slices of bacon or ham (fat trimmed off).
Bake at 350° oven 45 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad with honey lemon dressing
directions: Toss bananas in 2 tablespoons lemon juice; drain and reserve lemon juice.
Layer bananas and remaining fruit in a bowl. Combine 1/4 cup honey and reserved lemon
juice.
Drizzle over fruit.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple together.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and stir well.
Add miniature marshmallows and pecan pieces. Let set overnight or mix early in morning.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: In large pan, combine celery, onion, carrots, pepper and chicken broth.
Boil until veggies are tender.
Add potatoes and cream.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add flour and butter mixture to thicken.
Simmer until thick.

title: chipped beef and dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Cut out center of French bread loaf and fill with mixture.
Serve on small pieces of bread.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add all other ingredients.
Mix, then pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8 x 8-inch pan with cooking spray. Melt butter and remove from heat.
Mix in sugar; cool.
Add egg. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and butter to mixture.
Blend in vanilla and walnuts.
Bake 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut while warm.

title: brownie biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease baking sheets or line with parchment paper. In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until smooth. Beat in eggs one at a time, then add vanilla and almond extracts. In another bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking powder. Add flour mixture to egg mixture and stir until combined. Mix in chips and nuts.

title: parmesan cheese dip
directions: If expecting guests you might want to add this to a tray of nuts, cookies, crackers, cheese, etc.

title: b.b.q. beef or pork
directions: Cook beef or pork, cool and shred/chop. Mix all ingredients and simmer for 2 hrs.

title: homecoming punch(slush)
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in a large 5 gallon bucket, using a little less water than for normal Kool-Aid.
Stir well.
Add Hawaiian Punch and pineapple-grapefruit juice.
Stir.
Set bucket in large freezer.
Stir about every hour until it is real slushy. Serves around 50.

title: quick cherry crunch
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and pour off excess.
Pour cherry mix into pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Also add chopped nuts.
Dribble remaining oleo over top.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: baltimore crab cakes
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients; shape into 6 patties.
Coat with flour; chill at least 1 hour.
Cook patties in butter in a skillet over medium-high heat 4 minutes on each side or until golden. Yield:
6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together. Freeze. Thaw 1 to 2 hours. Add 2 to 3 bottles of ginger ale.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Place in round bowl and chill overnight.
Serve with Town House crackers.
Yields 50 servings.

title: fruit bar cookies
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In bowl, beat eggs.
Fold in powdered sugar and melted oleo.
Then fold in flour mixture, dates, nuts and candied fruit.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put glaze on top.
Mix powdered sugar, warm water, vanilla and a little oleo until blended.
Pour glaze over warm bars.

title: chicken with onion, potatoes and peppers
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 of the cayenne pepper, black pepper and paprika and 1/2 the garlic and oregano in bottom of pan.
Place chicken pieces in pan.
Place potatoes over chicken.
Layer onions and peppers over chicken and potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining spices and garlic over top.
Add about 1 cup water to pan; cover.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, sauce, cheeses and veggies, using whichever layers you like.
Make 3 to 4 layers, ending with sauce.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Cook on High power 8 minutes and on Medium-Low power 32 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 30 minutes.
(Use microwave with turntable.)

title: dip for veggies
directions: Take all the ingredients and mix well.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Melt butter; saute onions and celery.
Stir in flour, stirring until smooth.
Add milk, broth and wine slowly, stirring to keep a smooth consistency.
Add cheese and melt.
Stir in crabmeat, parsley, pimento and green onions.
Season to taste. Cook on low heat about 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers, keeping dip hot in a chafing dish.
This can also be used as a filling for patty shells.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, milk and melted butter and beat well.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°. Serve with vanilla or lemon sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy ice cream pie
directions: Crumble Oreos and spread in 9 x 13-inch pyrex dish.
Spread softened ice cream on top.
Pour chocolate syrup over ice cream and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.
Serves 15.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine the warm water and yeast in a large bowl.
Let stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes.
Stir in butter, sugar, eggs and salt.
Beat in flour,1 cup at a time, until dough is too stiff to mix (may need to add some flour).
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or up to 4 days.
Grease a 13x9-inch baking pan.
Turn the chilled dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Divide the dough into 24 equal-size pieces.
Roll each piece into a smooth ball, place balls in even rows in the prepared pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Bake until rolls are golden brown,15-20 minutes.
If desired, brush with melted butter.
Break rolls apart and serve.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: kiwi cheesecake tarts
directions: Peel two of the kiwi fruits.
In blender container, puree the 2 kiwi fruits (should be about 2 cups).
In a small saucepan, combine kiwi puree, lime peel and lime juice.
Bring just to boiling; reduce heat and cook 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Rinse blender container.
In blender container, combine cottage cheese, sugar, egg and cornstarch; cover and blend until smooth.
Add kiwi fruit mixture; blend until combined.
Pour into individual tart shells.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Peel and slice remaining kiwi fruits and arrange on top of tarts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving out 1/2 package of stuffing mix and the butter.
Place in greased casserole.
Mix butter and other 1/2 package of stuffing mix.
Top the casserole with this mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, salt, drain and mash.
Pour melted butter over dressing.
Divide and put layer of dressing in bottom of casserole.
To the squash, add pimentos, onion, sour cream, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole and put remaining herb dressing on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, almonds, celery, green onions and grapes in bowl. Add mixture of mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well. Stir in noodles immediately before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites. Add 1 tablespoon sugar to each egg yolk.
Put in oven and brown. Cook until thick.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Heat oven
Grease 2-quart round casserole.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole and bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beautiful broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli flowerets in small pieces.
Chop onion and add to broccoli.
Add raisins, sunflower seeds or cashews and crumbled bacon.
Mix well.
In small bowl,
mix mayonnaise or salad dressing, 1/2 cup sugar and the vinegar.
Toss with the broccoli.
Refrigerate.
Not only is this salad pretty, it's good.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine lukewarm water, sugar, salt and shortening in bowl. Add yeast; let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Add 1 egg; add flour to mixture. Keep in refrigerator and form into rolls as needed. Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark in crock-pot or slow-cooker.
Add chocolate chips.
After chips are melted, stir in peanuts.
Spoon out on waxed paper to cool and set.

title: 3 layer salad
directions: Dissolve 2 boxes jello in 4 cups boiling water and chill until firm in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve unflavored gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Scald milk and sugar.
Beat in cream cheese, then fold this gelatine, vanilla and nuts in.
Pour on top of strawberry layer and chill until firm.

title: hearty herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; then cover.
Let simmer one hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking, as nearly all the liquid will be absorbed by lentils and rice.
Serves 4.

title: hillbilly beans
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onion together.
Mix well the brown sugar, catsup, molasses or honey, barbecue sauce, chili powder, pepper and salt and add to cooked ground beef, bacon and onion.
Then add pork and beans, kidney beans and butter beans. You can use beans of your choice; I do.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°. We just love this and it is great to take out.

title: grilled chicken
directions: A gas or regular grill can be used.
Melt butter with cloves of garlic (finely chopped), rosemary, basil and juice of lemon or lime; fresh ginger root is also good to add.
Coat chicken with black pepper and seasoned salt or garlic powder.
Sear chicken on hot grill and baste with butter mixture.
Will take 25 to 30 minutes if it is a small broiler, cut in half.

title: strawberry punch(must be made 1 day in advance.)
directions: In a 6-quart container, mix together first 7 ingredients. Loosely cover and freeze until firm.
Remove punch 4 hours before serving.
Partially thaw.
To serve, break into chunks, add ginger ale and stir until slushy.

title: tartare canapes
directions: Cook ground beef and onions together until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on thin rounds of rye bread or pumpernickel.

title: grandma's popcorn balls
directions: Put sugar, syrup, water and butter in saucepan and cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until syrup forms a brittle ball in cold water or 270°. Add vanilla and stir to mix.
Pour over popped corn.
Wet hands when making balls.
Makes 12 medium size balls.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown beef well and drain off fat. Put ground beef and all remaining ingredients in crock-pot. Stir well. Cover and cook on high 1 hour, stirring until cheese is fully melted.
Serve immediately or turn to low for serving up to 6 hours later. Serve with tortillas or corn chips.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator. Drain well before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: autumn pork chop dinner
directions: In skillet, heat oil on high.
Brown chops on both sides. Remove and set aside.

title: hawaiian cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle 3 tablespoons graham cracker crumbs on bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Soften gelatin in water.
Drain pineapple tidbits, reserving juice.
Add enough water to make 3/4 cup and bring to boil.
Dissolve gelatin.
In small bowl mix cottage cheese at high speed until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Add egg yolks, milk, lemon juice, Sweet*10, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Blend in dissolved gelatin.
Chill until mixture is thick, but not set. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gently fold in gelatin.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil large hen with 4 bay leaves.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Remove all bones from chicken and dice.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add to butter and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry layer cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions, using a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Cool completely.
Spread cake with raspberry jam.
In a microwave or double boiler, melt chocolate chips; stir in milk and extract.
Fold in whipped topping.
Frost cake with chocolate topping.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs, and butter together.
Spread into a greased 9x13 inch baking pan.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese, and remaining eggs together in a mixing bowl.
Blend well. Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 40-45 minutes.
Cool.

title: rice sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain off all fat and crumble.
Finely chop onion, celery and green pepper and saute in small amount of sausage fat until limp, but not brown.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend carrots until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole 45 minutes at 350°.
To test, insert knife (like pumpkin pie).

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add milk and margarine (melted).
Add flavoring. Pour into unbaked pie crust and cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Recipe makes 2 pies.

title: how to freeze corn
directions: Bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pack in bags liquid and corn, then freeze.

title: baked french onion soup
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in oleo about 20 minutes.
Add broth, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with toast.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler or in microwave to melt cheese.

title: chocolate humps
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water, stir 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in vinegar.
Cover and chill the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients.
Pour mixture into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold and cover with aluminum foil.
Chill until firm.
Mold onto a lettuce-lined plate.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Place butter in roasting pan in 375° oven.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings and roll in flour.
When butter is completely melted, place chicken pieces, meaty side down, in a single layer. Bake 30 minutes and turn all pieces.
Bake another 30 minutes. Remove to paper towel covered dish and serve.

title: lunch box pizza
directions: Place 2 paper towels on microwave-safe plate.
Put pepperoni slices in a single layer and cover with 1 more paper towel. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Cut bread slices into 1-inch wide strips with kitchen scissors.
Put into plastic bag.
Put Ragu pizza sauce in plastic cup with lid.
Place pepperoni and cheese into another container. At lunch, put pepperoni and cheese in a bread strip. Fold over, dip in sauce and eat!
Kid original.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wipe brisket with damp paper towel and place in large kettle. Cover with cold water and add garlic clove, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Skim surface.
Cover kettle and simmer for 3 to 4 hours or until fork-tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions during the last 25 minutes.
Add cabbage wedges during the last 15 minutes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Slice corned beef thinly across the grain.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix
butter
with
flour and nuts.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: date-filled oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in oats and vanilla.
Roll cookie dough to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 2-inch round cutter and place half of cookies on a greased cookie sheet.
Place about 1 teaspoon Date Filling on each cookie; top with another cookie.
Press edges together with a fork.
Combine cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar; sprinkle on top of cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and immediately pour pineapple and juice on top.
Cool cake.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and milk.
Frost cake and refrigerate.

title: apple carrot salad
directions: Mix together.
Add enough mayonnaise to coat the ingredients. Chill.

title: pesto salmon soup
directions: Saute onions, celery, basil, parsley and garlic in butter and oleo.
Add Parmesan cheese, sugar, ginger and flour.
Cook until it thickens.
Puree all of this in a processor.
Return to pan.
Add fish stock and cool until it thickens.
Add whipping cream and salmon.
If mixture is too thick, add enough milk to thin to desired consistency.
Heat through gently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix together and form small balls; roll into coconut, powdered sugar and crushed nuts.

title: beef rolls
directions: Place steak slices between 2 sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound steak to 1/8-inch thick.
In a small bowl, combine parsley, basil, cheese and garlic; set aside.
Season pounded steak with salt and pepper; place a ham slice on each steak piece, trimming to fit if necessary.
Put a little reserved herb mixture at one end of each slice.
Roll up steak and ham slices, enclosing herb mixture; secure with wooden picks or kitchen string.
Heat olive oil in a large saucepan.
Add onion; saute 5 minutes or until soft.
Add beef rolls; saute 5 minutes or until evenly browned, turning occasionally.
Add wine, stock or water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender. Remove rolls from sauce; remove wooden picks or string.
Place on a warm serving platter.
Pour sauce over rolls.
Garnish with parsley or basil.
Serve with a dry red wine.
Makes 2 servings.

title: finger salad
directions: Spread out crescent rolls on 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley dressing together.
Spread mixture on crescent rolls.
Mix vegetables together; sprinkle on top of mixture.
Refrigerate. Cut in squares, if desired.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top before serving.

title: sausage-kraut bake
directions: In a large, flat baking dish, layer the drained sauerkraut, then a layer of browned Jimmy Dean sausage.
Top with a layer of mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle top thickly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until heated through.
The flavors blend marvelously and even kids like it.

title: champion new york cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese, sour cream, butter and eggs stand at room temperature for about 1 hour.

title: recipe for living
directions: Saute love and understanding until tender.
Mix well and continue cooking gently.
In a large bowl, blend willpower and determination well to avoid procrastination, adding a dash of flexibility to accommodate life's delicate variations.
Fold in a few leaves of awareness (more, if you savor knowledge).
Set aside to rise and expand its flavor throughout the days.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In greased casserole, put rice and pour water over it.
Mix together celery soup, mushroom soup and chicken soup plus dry onion mix and 1/4 cup water.
Pour 1/2 of this sauce over rice in casserole.
Place chicken pieces on top of this and pour remaining half of sauce over all.
Bake covered 2 hours at 275°.
Remove cover.
Bake additional 20 minutes to brown.

title: miniature chocolate tortes
directions: Cream Cheese Mixture:
Beat cream cheese, eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: squash jam
directions: Mix grated squash with lemon juice.
Microwave for 30 minutes on High, turning it. Add jello and sugar (we like apricot or peach flavored jello the best).
Microwave 8 minutes on Low.
Put in jars and seal.
This will look runny and will appear that it hasn't set up, but store a jar in refrigerator before opening; the cool makes it set up.
Store in refrigerator after opening.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish at 380° for 45 minutes.
May be refrigerated before baking.

title: chicken with sweet peppers and balsamic vinegar
directions: Season the chicken with salt and pepper. In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil. Saute the chicken over medium-high heat, turning once, until golden on both sides. Transfer the chicken to a plate.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam; set aside.
Mix together all the ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and cut into squares.
Serve while hot.

title: natillas
directions: Place egg yolks, flour and 1 cup milk in a small mixing bowl. Stir
to
make
a
smooth paste.
Set aside.
Place the remaining milk, sugar and salt in medium size pan and scald at medium
heat. Add
egg mixture to the scalded milk.
Continue to
cook
at medium
heat
until
a soft custard consistency. Remove
from heat
and
allow to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff
and
fold into custard.
Chill and garnish with nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: jovita's breakfast pizzawarren, texas
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Grease 9 X 13 pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla; stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and peppers in oil in a large skillet.
Add broccoli, carrots, tomato sauce, bay leaf, basil and salt.
Blend thoroughly.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook vegetables until just tender.
Will take about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and egg yolks.
Add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped egg whites.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown meat; season to your taste.
Drain off grease.
Stir in paste and sauce, then tomatoes and chili beans.
Add macaroni. Simmer until nice and hot, then serve with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and vanilla; add chocolate chips.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: claremont salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Combine dressing ingredients.
Use a jar with a top so that you can shake it to mix well.
Add dressing to salad; toss.
Marinate at least 24 hours.
